title: major meal lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and drain grease. Cook lasagna noodles; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat and let simmer over low heat.
Grate Mozzarella cheese; set aside.
Add 1 beaten egg to cottage cheese; set aside.
In casserole dish, lightly grease sides and bottom of dish.
Place ground meat mixture on bottom of pan, then noodles, cottage cheese, then Mozzarella cheese.
Then repeat.
If any meat mixture is left, put on top of casserole.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese; cover well.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbling on top. Turn broiler on; place dish under broiler until lightly browned on top.
Watch closely as not to burn.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot fruit bake
directions: Drain fruit.
Layer pineapple, apricots, peaches, apple rings and pears in glass baking dish.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and cornstarch; mix well.
Stir in sherry gradually.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over fruit.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve as a breakfast side dish.

title: brown sugar pecan pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: conley's casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in oil until soft.
Add chopped hamburger.
Cook until brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain fat.
In a large casserole bowl (oven proof), add soups together. Mix well.
Add meat mixture to soups.
Top with 1 can chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy icebox lemon pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Chill for several hours in refrigerator.
Additional lemon juice may be added for a more lemony taste.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift together the plain flour, salt and baking powder.
In a large bowl, mix Crisco, sugar and eggs, one at a time; beat well after each egg.
Add dry ingredients with sweet milk (alternating).
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hot rolls(icebox)
directions: Scald milk,
sugar and shortening; set aside to cool to room temperature.
Then	add
yeast that has been dissolved in the milk mixture.
Add
enough
flour to make a thick batter. Beat well. Let
rise
until
double
in size (about 2 hours). Then add baking powder, salt and soda.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Knead and make
into rolls.
Let rise 1 hour or more. Bake in moderate oven.

title: cajun pork braid
directions: Brown ground pork, drain.
Add celery, bell pepper, onion, garlic and cook until tender.
Stir in cream cheese, salt, ground red pepper, parsley and green onion.
Cook approximately 15 minutes, or until cream cheese is very soft and all ingredients well combined.

title: chicken with apricot glaze
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Coat with flour.
In a large skillet, brown each piece in heated margarine and oil.
After browning, coat chicken pieces with apricot jam.
Combine marjoram, lemon rind, soy sauce and apricot juice.
Pour over chicken.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Start by salting skillet; brown pork chops without adding oil. Chop up onion and brown as grease from pork chops becomes available. Pour in enough Minute rice to fill pan, laying in, under and between pork chops, etc. Stir around in grease so rice will be brown. Minute rice will not really swell so you can fill the pan quite fill. Pour in beef broth and cover tightly. Simmer until tender. Season as desired. It also can be baked after adding liquid.

title: fish batter
directions: Beat egg.
Add beer and stir.
Blend in dry ingredients.

title: snack
directions: Mix melted oleo, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in 4 teaspoons Parmesan cheese.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Cool. Makes 8 servings; each equals 1 bread and 1 fat.

title: g-daddy's quick and easy dressing and gravy(great served with chicken or turkey)
directions: Place contents of vegetable/seasoning packet and 1/2 stick of butter (cut into pieces) in a 1-quart casserole or an 8-inch square baking pan.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water; stir just to blend and partially melt butter.
Add stuffing crumbs; stir just to moisten.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 minutes (directions on back of box).

title: spiced whole pears
directions: Bring sugar, water, vinegar and spice (in bag) to a boil and boil several minutes. Add whole pears and cook until done.
Place in jars and seal.

title: chicken veloute sauce
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring to blend well.
Gradually add stock and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add cream and heat through.
Good served over sauteed or grilled chicken.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; let cool somewhat, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots slightly.
Drain and cool.
Mix all and marinate for 12 hours before serving.
Keeps well in fridge.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 14-inch pan over vanilla wafers or pour over graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: stars and stripes
directions: Slice 1 cup of strawberries and halve the remaining strawberries; set aside.

title: lemon-broccoli chick
directions: Coat skillet with oil.
Cook in skillet until brown on all sides (about 10 minutes).
Combine soup and milk; stir in juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until fork-tender.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Place strawberries, honey and a small amount of milk in blender.
Puree until almost smooth.
Add remaining milk and ice cream.
Blend until smooth and frothy, about 1 minute.
Serve in tall, chilled glasses garnished with fresh strawberries.
Yields 4 glasses.

title: brown gravy
directions: In a frying pan, cook onion in butter until lightly browned. Remove onion and discard.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly until butter is browned.
In a bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Add to butter.
Cook until flour is browned.
Slowly add stock, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes. Yield: Approximately 1 cup.

title: gigi's crock-pot bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain beans.
Put all ingredients in 5 to 6-quart crock-pot and add water to top.
Cover, turn on high and cook for 6 to 8 hours (or longer).
Mash beans lightly after about 3 hours of cooking to thicken the soup.

title: lasagne
directions: Boil lasagne noodles in water with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Strain; set aside to cool.
Brown ground beef; drain.
In large lasagne pan, layer the sauce, noodles, ground beef, cottage cheese, mushrooms and Mozzarella, then sauce, noodles, ground beef, cottage cheese, mushrooms and Mozzarella.
Repeat until gone.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a bowl; set aside.
Cook ground beef until browned; drain well and set aside.
Pour 1/2 of cornbread mixture into a greased 10 1/2-inch iron skillet. Sprinkle evenly with beef.
Top with cheese, onion and peppers. Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Chop onions and dried beef.
Mix all ingredients and shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot monterey rice salad
directions: Cook meat in lightly greased skillet until done (drain well). Add garlic salt, pepper sauce and lemon juice to mayonnaise.
Stir into meat mixture with remaining ingredients, except corn chips. Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Top with corn chips. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ray's original stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut out stems in mushrooms; chop finely.
Put aside.
Brown sausage and crumble.
Drain well.
Add to sausage mushrooms stems, garlic, basil, Dale's steak sauce and bread crumbs.
Mix together well.
Put a little butter and steak sauce in mushrooms, then stuff with sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes. Regulate ingredients to your taste.

title: skillet cajun catfish
directions: Put greens and water in skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in broth, rice, cumin and thyme.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 12 minutes, stirring once.
Place fillets on top of rice.
Cover; cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: western style bean casserole
directions: Drain last 3 cans of beans.
Fry bacon; drain and break into small pieces.
Brown hamburger, onion, green pepper and garlic. Add salt, pepper, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, catsup, bacon, vinegar and beans.
Cover and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until bubbling and heated through.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
This can also be prepared in a crock-pot approximately 3 to 4 hours or until heated thoroughly and bubbling.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemony chicken breast for 2
directions: Coat chicken with a mixture of the flour and salt.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned and no longer pink in the middle. Remove to a serving platter or dinner plates.
Add chicken broth and lemon juice to skillet.
Stir over medium-high heat for 2 or 3 minutes, until sauce is reduced slightly.
Stir in capers and parsley.
Pour over chicken.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix warm water and oatmeal; let set for 15 minutes.
Mix and dissolve yeast in water.
Add dissolved yeast mixture.
Stir in oil, sweetener and salt.
Mix in wheat flour and 3 cups unbleached flour.
Add more flour as needed. Knead on floured board until smooth and elastic.
Let rise; put in 2 loaf pans.
Let rise again in pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place about 1/3 Ritz crackers in bottom of casserole dish. Put the asparagus pieces (drained) on top of crackers.
Mix 1/2 cup water with soup and pour over asparagus.
Cover top with more Ritz crackers. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Melt margarine and add cracker crumbs. Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add milk to Dream Whip and beat until well blended. Line pan with crumbs. Add cherries on top of crumbs. Put Dream Whip mixture on top of cherries. Sprinkle crumbs on top. Chill overnight.

title: blueberry cupcakes
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend together both mixtures.
Add milk.
Put in blueberries.
Stir just until blended.
Put into lined cupcake tins.
Bake until done, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa, remove from heat and stir in sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well, add flour, salt, chopped nuts and vanilla. Mix well.
Spoon batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with the marshmallows while hot, cover with Chocolate Frosting.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Stir first four ingredients together over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients. Cool.
Spread on cake.

title: aunt ruthie's chicken
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and Lipton onion soup; cover chicken parts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots in 1/4-inch round slices.
Microwave 20 minutes. Arrange in layers (in large container with tight lid) with onion slices.
Bring tomato soup to a boil with oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over carrots and onions. Refrigerate until flavors are absorbed.

title: cherry peek-a-boo
directions: Cream together softened margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts. Spread 3/4 of mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Spoon remaining dough on top by teaspoons. About 12 teaspoons.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quick pasta sauce with black olives
directions: Saute garlic in oil, add olives, then rest of ingredients. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer slowly as you cook pasta.
Drain pasta, cover with sauce and serve hot.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and sugar in large bowl of electric mixer.
Mix well.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, stirring just until all ingredients are moistened.
Fold in strawberries and pecans.
Spoon mixture into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, stir together eggs, corn syrup, sugar, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: luscious lemon dessert
directions: Mix butter, flour and pecans together and press into an 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Whip cream cheese with mixer until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar and lemon extract. Blend well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over cooled crust.

title: ranch stew
directions: Dump all in large pot including liquid from vegetables. Simmer all day.
Works great in a crock-pot.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk, mix well.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat. Stir a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks then return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes more, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.

title: linguini with tomato, cream and basil sauce
directions: Heat oil in large skillet (medium heat).
Add onions and cook until soft and transparent.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes. Strain tomatoes by rubbing sides of strainer with a spoon to release as much juice as possible, then add to skillet.
Also, add basil, oregano and parsley.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and cook until some of the liquid has evaporated (about 10 minutes).

title: grape-nut custard
directions: Pour milk into well-beaten eggs and stir into mixed dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and stir.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Before baking, place pudding dish in a shallow dish of water.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in top of double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper until dry.

title: swiss and ham biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Slice 1 package of dinner rolls and spread 1/2 the mixture on top and 1/2 on bottom in between the rolls.
Layer ham and Swiss cheese.
Replace top of rolls and bake at 325° until warm.

title: hamburger pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onions, drain.
Simmer tomatoes, taco sauce, beans and chili powder.
Pour tomato mixture and ground beef into a deep baking dish.
Mix the meal, flour, egg and enough milk to make a thin batter.
Pour batter over meat and tomato mixture. Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: muffin squares
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients; beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Pour batter into greased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Bake about 20 minutes.
While warm, cut into squares.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Peel fruit; sweeten to taste.
Cook slow in juice until tender.
Do
not add water.
Use cornstarch dissolved in water to thicken.

title: california salad
directions: Drain fruit. Combine with other ingredients. Chill 24 hours. Serve on crisp salad greens.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel eggplant; cut up into pieces.
Dice a small onion and boil together until tender.
Drain and mash.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix butter, flour and milk.
Add cheese, bread crumbs, catsup and eggs.
Mix well and add all this to mashed eggplant. Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° for about 40 minutes until brown on top.

title: dana houston cajun beans
directions: Cook bacon and sausage until halfway done and 1 tablespoon hot sauce.
Add onions, green peppers and celery until soft.
Add beans, 1/2 minced garlic, little liquid smoke.
Go slow and taste. Add more liquid smoke and hot sauce to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes or until ready to eat.

title: curried chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken with onion, celery, parsley, bay leaf and seasoned salt for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cook broccoli as directed on package but slightly underdone.
Arrange in 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle almonds over broccoli. Remove bones from chicken and cut up.
Place chicken over broccoli.

In a bowl, mix together mayonnaise, soup and curry powder. Spread mixture over casserole and top with crumbs. Bake, uncovered, for approximately 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven or until brown and bubbly on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: zucchini and cheese casserole
directions: Wash and cut the zucchini into 1/2-inch cubes. Put into a saucepan and cover with water. Cook 6 to 8 minutes or until tender. Drain. Put back into saucepan. Add the cheese, salt, pepper and margarine. Stir lightly until cheese melts. Pour into a greased baking dish and sprinkle the Club cracker crumbs over the top. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: salad dressing
directions: Grind and mix together with a beater the carrots, onion, green peppers and pimentos. Combine salad oil, vinegar, sugar and salt with vegetable mixture.
Store in glass jar in refrigerator. Makes 1 quart.

title: california blend vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables as directed; drain and pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish; put sliced cheese on top.
Melt butter; add crushed crackers.
Put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is bubbling.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix topping with hands. Sprinkle over filling. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler(from a good friend, ruby griffin)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add milk.
Melt margarine in a 10 x 15-inch baking dish and add mixture, then add fruit evenly over dish.
I like peaches, usually two 1 pound butter tubs of frozen or a 29 ounce can.
Prepare fresh or frozen fruit by adding a half cup of extra sugar and bringing to a boil.

title: nutty peanut butter  christmas fudge
directions: Combine evaporated milk, butter, sugar and Marshmallow Creme in a heavy 2 3/4-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil. Continue cooking and stirring 5 minutes; remove from heat. Immediately add peanut butter chips and vanilla, stirring until chips are melted. Add nuts. Pour into a buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan. Cool. Makes about 3 pounds.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Beat in blender for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour over London Broil and marinade overnight or for 4 to 5 hours.
Baste while cooking. Use on chicken or beef.
Great on grill.

title: heavenly orange fluff
directions: Dissolve orange jello in boiling water.
Add orange juice, pineapple (plus juice) and mandarin oranges.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: french toast
directions: Arrange bread slices in single layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan with deep sides.
Beat the next 6 ingredients until well blended.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Grease a large pan. Transfer bread to pan without slices touching.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until puffed and lightly browned.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.
Bake at 425°.

title: annemarie's fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wipe a jelly roll pan with vegetable oil. Line pan with parchment paper that also has been wiped with oil.

title: dad baughman's beans
directions: Wash
beans.
Put
in
big pot.
Add pepper, garlic and chili powder.
Cover
with
quarts lukewarm water and cook gently for
1 hour.
Add the bacon, cut in one-inch cubes and cook slowly for about 2 hours or until tender.	Stir carefully and
add boiling
water (when needed).
Add the salt the last half hour before serving.
Serves 20.

title: surprise cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions and bake on a greased cookie sheet.

title: fruit cocktail bars
directions: Mix together and put in cookie sheet with edge on it.
Sprinkle top with coconut and walnuts.
Bake at 350° until done.
Put glaze on last.

title: raspberry mint punch
directions: Combine ingredients in punch bowl. Serves 14.

title: peach cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in batter with 2 knives.
Beat egg and add to milk.
Mix all together.
Grease two 9-inch cake pans.
Press dough in pan like you would pizza dough.
Place sliced peaches on top of dough.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: salsa bean salad
directions: Combine all beans, onions and pepper in large bowl.
Combine salsa, dressing, sugar and salt and pour over bean mixture.
Chill 24 hours, stirring often.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in butter.
Beat together eggs and milk. Blend into mixture just enough to moisten flour.
Do not overmix. Fold in banana and chopped nuts.
Spoon batter into 12 greased medium-sized muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, cereal, milk, salt and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into buttered baking dish; dot with small bits of the butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl; place in a baking pan.
Place about 6 large bay leaves on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: candy puffs
directions: Beat egg whites and vanilla until peaks form.
Set mixer and beat 15 minutes.
Fold in nuts and spoon onto waxed paper on cookie sheet.
Bake 45 minutes at 250°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt butter; add milk and egg yolks. Add dry ingredients and cook slowly, until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour into 8-inch pie shells.
Top with meringue.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Yields 2 pies.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix
sausage,
noodles,
milk, pepper, soup and cheese. Pour in	casserole
dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in 12 x 18-inch pan, greased well with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and let cool.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer each ingredient above.
Then grate longhorn cheese on top and chill.

title: peanut butter and jelly muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in peanut butter with 2 knives or a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and eggs all at once, stirring until flour is moistened.
Place 2 tablespoons of batter in greased, fluted or plain muffin cups. Place 1 teaspoon preserves in center of batter and top with 2 tablespoons more batter.
Repeat, making 12 muffins.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes.

title: venison (deer) stew
directions: Cook bacon.
Brown deer meat, salt and pepper in grease.
Add crumbled bacon.
Add onion, bell pepper, Veg-All, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and celery.
Let cook until done.
Add brown gravy mix and beef stew seasoning after everything else is done.
Add cornstarch or flour if it is not thick enough.
You can use beef bouillon cubes instead of beef stew seasoning.
Makes a large pot. May be cooked in a crock-pot overnight.

title: spinach-feta cheese pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Make pesto sauce according to package directions.
In bowl, combine pesto sauce with thawed, drained spinach.
Stir in Feta cheese.
Spread spinach mixture over crust. Top with shredded Mozzarella.
Place pizza directly on oven rack and bake for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: green beans with zucchini and bacon
directions: Saute bacon until crisp, drain, crumble and set aside.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add zucchini, green beans, salt and pepper and cook until crisp-tender.
Stir in crumbled bacon.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In saucepan, blend oleo, flour, salt and pepper together.
Add milk, one cup at a time, stirring until sauce is thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Mix with macaroni. Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except pastry shell).
Pour into pastry shell.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the broccoli, potato, onion and diluted broth. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook until tender (about 6 minutes). In a small bowl, whisk the milk into the flour. Add this mixture to the soup, along with the tarragon, thyme, salt and pepper. Stir constantly until the mixture comes to a boil and is thick (about 7 minutes). Ladle into bowls, and sprinkle with cheese and red pepper.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch (or flour) and salt in top of double boiler.
Stir in cold milk; cook over boiling water (stirring constantly) until thickened.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer. Stir a little of hot mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add remaining mixture into double boiler and cook for 2 minutes over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir constantly.
Cool and add vanilla. Pour into baked shell.
If desired, cover with meringue and bake at 325° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned or just before serving top with whipped cream.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and spices.

title: barb's exquisite crabmeat quiche
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, milk, green onions, Swiss cheese, jalapeno pepper cheese, flour and eggs; fold in crabmeat.
Pour all ingredients into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Cut into pie slices. Serves 8.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and picante sauce in processor. Garnish with green onions. Serve with corn chips. Makes 2 cups.

title: dreamsicle cooler
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on low speed.
May also be frozen into pops.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil 4 cups sugar and water 3 minutes; cool.
Add orange juice, juice of lemons, pineapple juice and bananas.
Mix well. Freeze.
When served, add 4 quarts ginger ale.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in alternately with milk; mix well and stir in blueberries gently.
Put into greased muffin tins or use cupcake liners.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: cinnamon sticky buns
directions: For 8-inch square pan (double, use 13 x 9-inch).

title: evelyn's breakfast
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into dish.
Refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: homemade gluten steaks
directions: Mix flour with just enough water to make a heavy dough.
Place this ball of dough in a large bowl and completely cover with water.
Let stand overnight.
Wash dough under running water until water is nearly clear.
If water is completely clear, the gluten tends to be tough.
Pull gluten into pieces that are about 4 inches in diameter and very thin.
Set aside.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Dip each corn tortilla in hot oil and layer them in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix the cottage cheese, sour cream, green chilies and black olives together; spread mixture on top of the tortillas.
Top with Cheddar and Jack cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Melt butter. Mix with crumbs. Press on the bottom of baking dish. Spread cherry pie mix over crumbs. Whip Dream Whip with sugar and milk. When it begins to thicken, beat in cream cheese. Spread over prepared cherry pie mix. Chill overnight.

title: bacon quiche biscuit cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, milk and eggs on low speed until smooth.
Stir in Swiss cheese and onions; set aside.

title: raspberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
In blender, mix cranberry sauce and sour cream.
Slowly add to cooled Jell-O.
Add raspberries, then pour into 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt margarine.
Add salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour Chex cereals, nuts and pretzels into large Ziploc bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture.
Seal top of bag securely.
Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated.
Transfer mixture to cookie sheet or roasting pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Makes 10 cups.

title: mama and aunt mandy's tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt margarine and cream into the above; beat in sugar, egg, vanilla and milk. Cream well.
Gradually add flour from an extra 1/2 cup flour until dough is stiff enough to roll.
Chill well.
Place on lightly floured board and roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with lightly floured cookie cutter and place on greased cookie sheet.
Prick tops with fork; sprinkle with a little granulated sugar (optional). Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Great all alone or with coffee or tea.

title: democrat salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients. Ready to eat.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix creamed butter, sugar, eggs, flour, soda and salt.
Crush bananas and add in.
Add nuts.
Grease bread pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Whip eggs lightly.
Combine with flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Mix smooth.
Add hot sauce.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and broccoli evenly over top.
Push below surface to keep from burning.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool 10 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together and set aside.
Bring to a boil the butter, cocoa, oil and water.
Add to buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Add flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Cook at 325° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Pour icing over cake while hot.
Cook in oblong pan. Leave in pan.

title: lime daiquiris
directions: Combine limeade and rum in blender.
With blender running, add ice cubes one at a time.
Blend until slushy.
Garnish with a piece of fresh fruit.

title: *just good slaw
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine the brown sugar, cornstarch, egg and vinegar and cook over low heat until thick.
Cool the mixture.
Combine with the salt, pepper, prepared mustard, cabbage and peppers.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: old fashioned gingersnaps
directions: Heat molasses and shortening.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture (need not wait to cool).
Thoroughly chill, toss on lightly floured board, roll very thin and cut. Handle quickly and do not let get warm.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken cordon bleu casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Top each breast with a slice of cheese and a slice of ham. Saute mushrooms with 2 tablespoons margarine if fresh. Omit if mushrooms are canned. Spread over chicken. Mix soup with spoon and pour over chicken. Toss dressing with 1/2 cup melted butter and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until browned. Serve with rice.

title: jello pudding dessert
directions: Bring water to boiling point.
Stir in pudding and jello. Boil about 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit. Put in pan and refrigerate.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in glass bowl in order listed.
Combine cream cheese, juice and rind.
Mix well.
Beat cream until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, fold in cream cheese mixture.
Spoon over fruit and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix orange juice, water and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients and freeze.
Thaw 2 hours before serving.

title: anne's cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll into shape.
Roll in pecans.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Place cabbage and apple in Dutch oven.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over cabbage.
Place lid on Dutch oven and simmer until tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp, crab, oyster and sausage gumbo
directions: Heat oil and butter to smoke.
Add flour; stir to dark red brown.
Add vegetables and garlic.
Add tomato puree; cook for 10 minutes.
Add water and seasonings; simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Chop sausage; saute in large pan.
When brown, pour off grease.
Add shrimp.
When they turn pink, add green onions and parsley.
Now, add this to the big pot that has been simmering. Add crabmeat and oyster water.
Adjust seasoning.
Add oysters to the hot Gumbo at the last minute.
Serve over hot, boiled rice. Makes 2 gallons.

title: three-layer salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar; spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: baked mostaccioli
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned and vegetables are tender. Drain. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, undrained mushrooms, water, salt, sugar, basil, pepper and bay leaf. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Stir in mostaccioli noodles (cooked). Turn half of the meat mixture into 3-quart casserole or 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, then half of the cheese, remaining meat mixture, then the rest of the cheese.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with brown sugar and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add beaten egg.
Spread and pour batter over all. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine baking mix, cheese and sausage in bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
24 servings.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Roll 1/2 of wafers and sprinkle in bottom of pan or dish (6 to 7-inch).
Beat eggs, butter and sugar together with egg beater until very thick and creamy.
Spread over wafer crumbs.
Whip cream very stiff.
Mix nuts and pineapple with cream.
Spread over butter mixture.
Roll remainder of wafers and sprinkle over top of cream, nuts and pineapple mixture.
Top with whipped cream. Chill.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt caramels in microwave.
Stir until smooth.
Warm the cream cheese, then stir into melted caramels.
Serve with apple slices. Must be refrigerated.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in butter until crisp.
Add onion and carrots; remove bacon.
Cook onion and carrots until tender.
Add salts, pepper and water; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine milk, cream and flour; cook until thick.
Add potatoes, bacon, parsley and clams with juice.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together the flour, 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cocoa.
Add milk, oil and vanilla.
Stir until smooth, then stir in nuts.
Turn into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring gradually until mixed.
Pour mixture over batter in pan.
Bake about 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Serve warm or chilled with vanilla ice cream.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
In a bowl, combine eggs, sugar, butter, flour, lemon juice and rhubarb.
Blend thoroughly. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 50 minutes, or until done.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all together and beat for 5 minutes.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cool for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers,	tomatoes
and
cauliflower in bite size pieces.
Make a brine
of
4 gallons of water and 1 pint salt. Add vegetables and
set
overnight.
In the morning, drain and cook vegetables until tender, not soft.

title: salad bar rice salad
directions: Cook rice; drain off whatever water is still left on and allow to cool.
Whip the cream and add the sugar.
Drain the pineapple and mix all ingredients together, mixing lightly.
Cover and chill three hours before serving.

title: butterscotch salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding mix over pineapple and mix well.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: sue's mashed potato cocoa cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and beat in sugar.
Then add beaten egg yolks, vanilla, mashed potatoes and cocoa.
Sift together cinnamon, salt, flour and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture, alternately with milk.
Add nut meats.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in a flat cake pan for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost with fudge frosting.

title: simple strawberry dessert
directions: In a large bowl, tear the cake into bite-size pieces.
Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, mix pudding according to package directions.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour pudding mixture over the cake pieces.
Top with sliced strawberries.
Spread the glaze on top of strawberries.
Chill and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in 2 to 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add to sauteed mixture the rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil and let simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Good with anything.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, oatmeal, onion, 1/2 cup catsup, milk, eggs, 1 tablespoon horseradish, salt and pepper in large mixing bowl; mix well.
Spoon into 10-inch plastic ring mold.
Microwave on Roast for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake by box directions.
Crumble in bottom of punch bowl. Top with instant pudding mix (made as box instructs).
Top with Cool Whip.

title: low-fat fettuccine alfredo
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Drain and put back into a hot pan.
In a food processor, process the cottage cheese until very smooth.
Add Parmesan cheese, milk, egg substitute, garlic, pepper, nutmeg and salt.
Process until very smooth.
Add cheese sauce to pasta and place pan over medium heat.
Cook 1 minute, stirring.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Mix the cream cheese, lemon juice, tarragon, garlic salt, pepper and shredded cooked chicken together.
Make two 6 x 6-inch squares with crescent rolls.
Put 1/2 of chicken mixture on each crescent roll square.
Bring corners together and pinch shut. Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: iced tea(sweetened)
directions: Put in gallon container and fill with water.
Better if made a day ahead.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Combine 2 cups milk with both boxes of pudding.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese with 1/4 cup milk.
It is best to leave cream cheese at room temperature before mixing in order to get all of chunks out.
Slowly combine 2 bowls and Cool Whip for final mixture.
Grind cookies with mixer and layer cookies, pudding, cookies, pudding, etc., topped with cookies.

title: nothings
directions: Cream well the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and flour and mix well.
Put dough on greased cookie sheet.
Score dough into squares with a knife.
In center of each square, spoon pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
You can use any kind of pie filling.
We like cherry for this.
Refrigerate them after cooled and cut.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything together and put into large casserole dish. Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for one hour.

title: raspberry-cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups of hot water.
Stir to dissolve.
Mix in cranberry sauce, breaking it up.
Mix in pineapple, including juice.
Refrigerate to set.

title: spinach pie
directions: In frying pan, saute a little oil, minced garlic and drained package of spinach.
Grease pie plate.
Sprinkle with flavored bread crumbs to cover entirely, forming a crust.

title: quiche
directions: Cook bacon and broccoli; chop onions.
Pour all in the pie shell.
Mix eggs, half and half, salt, nutmeg, both peppers (just a dash).
Add cheese.
Make a hole in the middle and pour the milk portion over it until it fills the pie.
Any leftover, toss out.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 1 cup strawberries.
Add enough water to make 2 cups. Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add to mashed berries. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon and jello.
Cool. Mix with strawberries.
Pour into pie shell. Chill.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Mix well and pour in well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sherry almond cake
directions: Mix together in Mixmaster for 2 minutes.

title: jeweled cheese ball
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except almonds.
Beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often, until well blended.
Shape mixture into large ball.
Roll in toasted almonds. Cover; refrigerate.
Remove from refrigerator 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yield:
1 cheese ball.

title: chili elbows
directions: Brown onion and beef in the margarine.	Add salt, chili powder, catsup, soup and water.
Cook slowly, 20 to 30 minutes or until
desired
thickness.	In the meantime, cook macaroni according
to
directions.	Place macaroni on platter or individual	plates.
Top
with
chili and serve.
Very good served with garlic bread, cheese, carrot sticks, etc.

title: spiced hot cider
directions: Put all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Heat and serve.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Drain the oranges, reserving the juice.

title: prickly pear jelly
directions: You will need a large pot, sieve, large bowl, potato masher, old toothbrush, 2 feet square of clean cloth and rubber gloves.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, add 3 bananas, sliced.

title: shannon's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar with an electric mixer.
Beat in egg and vanilla extract.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
The dough will be very stiff; blend in last 3/4 cup flour by hand.
Do not chill dough.
Divide dough into two balls.
On a floured surface, roll each ball into a circle 12-inches in diameter and 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out cookie shapes, dipping cutters in flour before each use.
Bake cookies on top rack of oven for 6 to 7 minutes, until cookies are lightly browned. Cool completely on wire racks.
Frost and decorate as desired.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with the pepper and garlic powder. Combine rice, chicken broth and soy sauce in 10-inch skillet. Stir.
Place chicken on top.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle chicken with a little soy sauce, then place pea pods on top of chicken.
Cover and remove from the heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Sift
flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together in a bowl and
set
aside.
In a large bowl beat eggs.
Add oil, buttermilk,
sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.	Add the dry ingredients
and
blend.
Add pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts. Mix well.
Pour
into
a
14-inch
Dutch
oven.
Bake
for 45 minutes.
For
the
first
25 minutes have 14 coals on the top and 12
on the bottom.
After 25 minutes remove coals from the bottom and leave 14 on the top for the rest of the time.
When cooked, glaze with glaze recipe.

title: pina colada sherbet
directions: In a blender container or food processor, combine cream of coconut, pineapple, orange juice and rum.
If using a processor, process only half of the ingredients at a time.
Cover; blend or process until nearly smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch baking dish or a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover; freeze several hours or until firm.
Break sherbet into pieces.
Place sherbet, half at a time, in a blender container or processor.
Cover; blend or process until fluffy or, if desired, place in a chilled bowl and beat with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Return pineapple mixture to pan. Cover and freeze at least 4 hours or until firm.

title: susan's golden apricot cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Spread the jam on the bottom layer of the cake.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook instant rice as directed. Add chili and onion. Cook in microwave on medium for 5 minutes or until hot.

title: sausage and macaroni
directions: Mix ingredients.
Heat and season to taste.
Tasty and easy on nights you need to eat in a hurry.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, margarine and 1 cup milk.
Blend well.
Take half of the mixture and press in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind berries and add cup sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes or until sugar has dissolved.	Dissolve lemon gelatin with water. Refrigerate until soft in middle, firm on the outside.
Blend with Dream Whip until fluffy; add berries and nuts.
Pour into bowl and chill until firm.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix and spread on and between layers.

title: rocky road cluster
directions: Melt milk chocolate in double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, pecans and chocolate chips.
Stir until coated.
Drop by spoons onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Store in cool place.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: high energy health shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender jar and blend for 60 seconds.
Serve immediately.
Yields 1 serving, 350 calories.

title: no roll pie dough(for 1 crust pies, makes 2 shells)
directions: Combine salt, flour and sugar in pie pan.
Whip the oil and milk with a fork.
Pour over mixture in pie pan.
Mix with fork or hands until moistened.

title: crumb coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly mixture forms. Reserve 1 cup of this for frosting.
Add the rest of the ingredients, egg, milk, vanilla, soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat and pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle 1 cup of crumbs on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
I bake longer than recipe says.
Sour the milk by putting 1 teaspoon of vinegar in it.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables 10 minutes.
Slice onion in while cooking vegetables.
Drain.
Heat soup to thin.

title: bacon appetizer croissants
directions: Open crescent rolls; separate into 8 rectangles and press perforations together.
Mix other ingredients together.
Spread 2 tablespoons cream cheese mixture on each rectangle.
Cut diagonally from one corner to other in each direction to form "X." Split "X" down center to form 6 triangles.
Fold pointed end of triangle toward wide end.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes on cookie sheet until golden.
Makes 4 dozen.
Serve warm.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar, eggs, orange juice and rind. Stir in sour milk. Sift dry ingredients together and stir in. Chill 1 hour, if desired. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup. Mix in pecan halves.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until set.
Cool before serving.

title: beef casserole
directions: In bacon grease or oil, cook bell pepper and diced onion until soft.
Mix roast beef and mushroom soup with pepper and onion. Top with cheese.

title: chicken or turkey divan
directions: Grease 9 x 13 baking pan with oleo. Layer broccoli cuts on bottom. Mix together chicken soup, curry powder, lemon juice and mayonnaise. Add to this mixture the cut up chicken or turkey. (Great recipe for leftover turkey.) Pour chicken (turkey) mixture over broccoli and spread out evenly. Mix together shredded Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs. Evenly distribute this mixture over top. Put dabs of oleo on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, and spices together. Pour over vegetables. Let stand 12-24 hours before serving. Will keep in refrigerator for 5-7 days. A good "prepare ahead" when expecting company.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine and mix well.
Shape into oval patties.
Place in deep dish.
Heat 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup, 1/2 cup milk and 1 tablespoon butter and garlic (as desired).
Pour over patties. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
During last 10 minutes, add 2 ounces sliced mushrooms, drained.

title: cornbread cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: best banana bread
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Beat in eggs and add salt.
Mash bananas with fork; add to mixture.
Add soda and flour last.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup mushroom soup, beef onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg.
In 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat mixture into 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Spoon off 2 tablespoons drippings and reserve.

title: pancakes (using biscuit mix)
directions: Stir mix and sugar together. Mix egg and water. Add to mix and sugar. Stir until dry ingredients are barely moistened.
Batter will by lumpy. Pour batter onto hot griddle or fry pan using about 3 tablespoons of batter. Cook until top is bubbly and edges begin to dry. Turn and brown other side.

title: sweet loaf bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. In a large bowl, combine sugars and oil; beat 1 minute. Add eggs, beating well. In a separate bowl, combine flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add to first mixture and stir to moisten. Fold in carrots, raisins and pecans. Pour into loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool for awhile before removing from pan.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread uncooked hamburger in bottom of 13 x 9 1/2-inch casserole.
Spread cream of mushroom over hamburger.
Layer cheese over hamburger and soup mixture.
Top with Tater Tots layered over all.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until Tater Tots are brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach by package directions and drain well. Place into 1-quart baking dish. Mix cream cheese, milk and onion and spoon over spinach. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pesto(for use on pasta, in salads or in soups)
directions: Mash the basil, spinach and garlic into a smooth paste.
Stir in, slowly, the cheese and softened butter.
Add the olive oil, little by little.
(We usually don't use a full 1/2 cup.)
Season with salt and black pepper.
This can be done in a blender, but mix all ingredients together before blending.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder; set aside.
Combine sugar, butter, shortening and eggs.
Beat 5 minutes.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring.
Beat 5 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: parsleyed new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Place in medium saucepan.
Add boiling water to measure 2 inches and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling. Boil gently, covered, for 20 minutes, or just until potatoes are tender.
Drain; return to heat several minutes to dry out.
Add butter, lemon juice, remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and the parsley; toss gently to coat well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mother's cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cocoa.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9-inch cake pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 60 minute reuben loaf
directions: Note:
If you use Fleischmann's regular active dry yeast, dissolve yeast in 1 cup water (105° to 115°).
Mix in margarine, sugar, salt and enough flour to make dough.
After kneading, cover and let rise in greased bowl over hot water 20 minutes.
Punch down, shape and let rise 20 minutes.
Bake as directed.

title: mildred debendarfer's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until very light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate milk and flour with baking powder.
Pour cake in pan, then add brown sugar and add sour cream or buttermilk.
Bake at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape loosely into small balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Put brown sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla into a mixing bowl; mix until well blended.
Spoon pineapple, measure accurately, and blend into sugar mixture.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir into sugar mixture.
Mix walnuts and raisins into batter.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 3 dozen.

title: aunt bee's dutch honey cake
directions: Mix the sugar, honey and eggs well.
Sift together the flours, baking soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients well together.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brenda's veggie pizza
directions: Press dough into jelly roll pan and bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until brown.
Layer with mixture of cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Sprinkle with veggies.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours until flavors mingle.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat 3 eggs on high speed 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice and stir.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold into pumpkin mixture. Spread in a greased paper lined cookie sheet.
Top with 1 cup walnuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out on sugared towel. Roll and cool.
Make filing of powdered sugar, cheese, butter and vanilla and spread over cooled, unrolled cake and roll again. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion together. Add soup and picante sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.
Layer in casserole dish with torn up tortillas. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing and place on flattened bread.
Remove crust on bread.
Roll and flatten bread with rolling pin.
Place one spear diagonally on bread.
Fold opposite corners of bread over spear; press closed.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken and spaghetti casserole
directions: Set chicken and 1 cup broth aside.
Boil spaghetti in remaining chicken broth. Saute green peppers, pimientos and mushrooms in 1/4 stick butter.
Mix with the 1 cup chicken broth. Layer all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Chop onion and garlic and saute in shortening.
Add paprika and pepper.
Mix meat, rice, onion, salt and water.
Core cabbage.
Place in boiling water, cutting leaves as they loosen. Fill each leaf with meat mixture.
Place layer of rolls in pot. Top with kraut.
Repeat until pan is filled.
Cover with tomatoes and water.
Cook 3 hours.

title: sugarless fruit cookies
directions: In a large pan, combine dates, apples, raisins and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Cool well.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break up cauliflower into small pieces and place in bowl. Crumble bacon on top. Sprinkle dry Italian dressing mix on top. Add a couple of large spoonfuls of mayonnaise. Mix well.

title: dip for shrimp
directions: Combine mustard, catsup and mayonnaise; beat with fork or wire whip.
Add cold salad oil very, very slowly (the secret to thickening the dip), beating constantly.
Add oil until thickened. Stir in all seasonings, mixing well.
Makes enough for 3 pounds of shrimp.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Slowly add milk last, to preferred consistency.
Refrigerate.

title: dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Cut off top of pumpkin and clean.
Brown ground beef.
Add soy sauce, sugar, mushrooms and soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add rice, chestnuts and onion.
Spoon mixture into pumpkin.
Replace top. Bake 1 hour at 350° on baking sheet.
Serve directly from the pumpkin, using it's meat as a vegetable.

title: ambrosia delight
directions: Combine all but Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.
Serve next day adding Cool Whip.

title: lumpia shanghai
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add egg, soy sauce and mix thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper.
At one end of lumpia wrapper, spoon about 2 Tbsp. of the pork mixture and roll tightly.
Brush one end of wrapper with water to seal.
Cut roll into 2 pieces.
Deep fry till golden brown.
Serve with hot sweet and sour sauce.

title: fanny mae fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar, vanilla and butter for 2 minutes stirring, turn off heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add chocolate one at a time until melted.
Makes 5 lbs.
Add nuts and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: summer pasta primavera
directions: Season chicken with salt (optional).
Spray non-stick Dutch oven or very large saucepan with cooking spray until bottom is well coated.
Over high heat, stir fry chicken in pan until it is no longer pink; remove and set aside.
Re-spray pan and over medium heat, saute onion, bell pepper and garlic until tender.
Return chicken to pan with mushrooms, squash, basil and pepper; saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in sauce and pasta; heat through and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dutchman's bowl(soup)
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and crumble. Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onion, parsley and thyme.
Cook until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind fresh cranberries in food chopper.
Combine sugar, water and cranberries and boil for 5 minutes, then add 1 small package cherry or strawberry Jell-O.
Dissolve good and add crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar until particles are fine in texture.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until set but not brown.
Combine eggs, brown sugar, coconut, pecans and vanilla extract.
Mix well and spread on partially baked dough.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes being careful not to overcook.
Frost immediately.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Warm over medium heat.
Simmer to keep hot.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak the poppy seed in the milk overnight.
Cream the sugar and butter. Add poppy seed mixture. Add the flour, baking powder, vanilla and egg whites.
Bake in two 8 or 9-inch layers at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup with roast beef
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot, season with salt, pepper and butter.
Cook slowly until it boils.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Cook and stir sausage and onion in oil until onion is tender. Stir in potatoes, sauce mix, water and pepper.
Heat to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Add carrots, cover and simmer until carrots are tender.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Cover and cook until broccoli is tender and cheese is melted.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat ground beef in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread soup over meat and cover with grated cheese.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° covered 45 minutes and uncovered 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat and simmer.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Butter dish first.
Melt together the first 3 ingredients. Pour over the marshmallows and peanuts.

title: bacon cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain.
Then add cream cheese to crumbled bacon. Spread onto bread and cut into finger size sandwiches.
Can cut the crust off, if desired.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix all well, adding nuts last.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake in 325° oven, about 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip or cover with cream cheese filling.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Grease casserole with oleo or spray with Pam.
Slice apples into dish.
Combine 3/4 cup of sugar with cinnamon to taste; sprinkle over apples.
Combine 3/4 cup flour with remaining 1/2 cup sugar and 1 stick of oleo.
I like to add 1/4 to 1/2 cup oatmeal to this mixture.
Crumble this over the apples.
Cook in moderate oven (about 350°) for approximately 45 minutes.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain salmon and remove skin and bones.
Mix with other ingredients except pecans and parsley.
Chill for a couple of hours so you can form a log, then roll the log in nuts and parsley.

title: butter cashew brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and water; boil to 280° on candy thermometer.
Add butter.
Cook to hard crack stage and add soda and cashew nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered jelly roll pan. Cool and break into pieces.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil onion and spaghetti in the juice from the chicken. Drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 350°
until cheese melts.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter; press into pie pan and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and lemon juice in large electric mixer bowl until smooth and creamy.
Pour into pie crust and bake 15 minutes at 300° or until done in center (test with toothpick).

title: orange julius drink
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender for 1 minute on high speed.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve in stem glasses.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.	Bake at 400° for
minutes
or
until
tests	done.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup and remaining ingredients.
Shape firmly into loaf; place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Blend remaining ingredients, 1/4 cup water and 2 tablespoons drippings.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Serve with meat loaf as a side sauce.
This is a family favorite.
We all like the tomato sauce to put on the meat-in place of catsup or steak sauce.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Stir pecans in butter and put in oven until toasted.
Cool. Combine ingredients; mix well.
Add cooled pecans.
Pour mixture in freezer and freeze until firm.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter and sugar; mix well.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Roll dough in 3/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with floured fork or press unwrapped Kiss in center.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: copper pennies (marinated carrots)
directions: Peel or scrape carrots and slice thin.
Boil 8 minutes, drain and allow to cool.
Combine salt, pepper and 1/4 cup oil and mustard, mix well.
Mix balance of oil, sugar, vinegar and soup, mix well.
Combine with first mixture and pour over carrots, onions and peppers.
Put in covered dish or jars, store in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep up to three weeks.

title: egg and cheese bake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, except butter.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour in cheese/egg mixture, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream cheese, oleo and powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: white velvet cut out cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar. Add sugar and egg yolks, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out on lightly floured board or linen tea towel.
Do not roll too thin.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Be careful not to overbake.

title: curried chicken cutlets
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness with meat mallet.
Combine 1 teaspoon curry powder and next 3 ingredients in shallow dish; dredge chicken in flour mixture and set aside.

title: baked kibbe
directions: Wash wheat and then soak in clear water for at least 30 minutes.
Then grind your meat again with onion, salt and pepper. Mix mixture thoroughly with the wheat.
Grease a shallow baking pan and put in a layer of the mixture; sprinkle with pine nuts and then add another layer.
After this is done, dot butter on top. Make a hole in the mixture in the center about the size of a quarter.
Bake in a hot oven, 425°, until the meat is golden brown.

title: unstuffed pepper soup
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, cook the beef, peppers and onions over a small medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain off excess grease. Stir in broth, soup, tomatoes and mushrooms.	Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for at least 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Add rice and heat thoroughly.

title: di's lemon mold
directions: Mix jello, sugar and boiling water.
Refrigerate until it starts to gel.
Check after one hour.
Add Cool Whip and lemonade; whip.
Put into mold.
Ready in 3 hours.

title: mom mom's blueberry cake
directions: Cook berries with 1/2 cup water for 5 minutes over medium heat. Drain off juice, reserving 1 cup.
Set berries and juice aside. Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, baking powder, butter and milk. Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Add berries over batter. Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar over berries.
Pour 1 cup juice over everything.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bob's banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and water.
Add instant pudding to milk and water mixture until smooth.
Refrigerate the pudding mix for 5 minutes to set.
While pudding is setting, whip the whipping cream. Slice the bananas.
Mix whipped cream with the set pudding.
Set aside about half a banana and 6 to 8 cookies.
Begin layering the ingredients in a large serving bowl, making 3 or 4 layers:
1) pudding/cream mixture; 2) cookies; 3) banana slices; 4) top off with pudding/cream mix.
Garnish top of pudding with rest of cookies and banana slices.
Refrigerate about an hour (unless you can't wait that long).

title: whole wheat sticks
directions: Add and mix all dry ingredients.
Drizzle oil over and rub with hands until well blended.
Add water; mix well.
Knead lightly.
Pat out on wax paper 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into strips, then cut across making about 3-inch sticks.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
These sticks are great for camping or traveling, as they keep for several weeks without refrigeration.

title: easy round steak
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1/2 cup of water.
Cut round steak in pieces and add to mixture.
Cook in crock-pot for 5 hours on high.

title: hot pepper spread
directions: Chop peppers in blender.
Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil in large canner.
Mix flour and enough water to make a thickening. Pour into other mixture and stir over medium heat until thick. Put in hot jars and seal.
Good on bologna, lunch meat, hot dogs, etc.

title: quick and easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add tomatoes, Manwich, mustard, onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Add sugar and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Wipe chops with damp paper towels; trim excess fat.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil on both sides until nicely browned. In hot oil in large skillet, saute onion and garlic, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, thyme, bay leaf, 3/4 teaspoon salt and pepper; mix.
Boil 3 quarts water with 1 teaspoon salt.
Add macaroni; cook for 10 minutes, or until tender; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Add macaroni to tomato mixture; mix.
Arrange chops on top.
Cover; bake for 40 minutes.

title: char's crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, Worcestershire, horseradish and Old Bay until well blended.
Fold in crabmeat and sprinkle top with Old Bay.
Bake in casserole for 35 to 40 minutes.
Will boil slightly.
Serve with crackers or warmed French bread.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco and salt into flour (like corn meal).
Beat eggs, water and vinegar together.
Pour over flour mixture; with a fork, stir lightly until flour is moist.
Makes three 2-crust pies or six 9-inch crusts.

title: corn salad cups
directions: With tip of knife, cut and discard stem end of tomato.
Cut off 1/2-inch slice from each and dice slices.
Place in small bowl.
Stir in corn, cucumber, dressing, oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill until cold.
Scoop seeds and pulp from tomatoes.
Wrap and refrigerate tomato shells until ready to serve.
Just before serving, fill tomato shells and garnish with parsley.

title: orange pineapple punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as recipe calls for; add pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.

title: snicker apple salad
directions: Stir all together and chill before serving.
Can be made day ahead.
The recipe doubled fills large Tupperware salad bowl.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, then add the eggs, flour, salt and soda.
Fold in the pecans and apples.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cavateena
directions: Cook noodles by directions.
Brown sausage or ground beef and drain.
Add sauces and heat.
Layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 sauce, 1/2 pepperoni and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add cream cheese, stirring over low heat until melted and incorporated with the sausage.
The mixture will be rather bland looking.
Add hot sauce if desired.
(Note: We usually add fresh black pepper here as well.)

title: beer barbecue sauce
directions: Combine the first nine ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in onion and lemon.
Remove from heat.
This is the sauce for barbecue ribs! Yields 3 cups.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix thawed frozen strawberries with canned strawberry pie filling.
Add a few sliced fresh strawberries to this mixture.
In a clear pedestal bowl layer 1/3 of cut up pieces of angel food cake.
Add 1 layer of strawberries mixture (about 1/3) and then layer 1/3 of the pudding.
Continue up the glass bowl until all ingredients are used.
Cover top with the whipped topping. Decorate with a few strawberries.
Can be made ahead.
Simple to do and makes a spectacular looking and delicious dessert.

title: mexican rice
directions: Rinse rice twice with water.
Toast rice until golden brown in pan with oil.
Stir rice constantly for an even toast.
Stir in onion.
Mix in water and tomatoes.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: You will need a 3 quart Pyrex or glass rectangular casserole dish.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat; season and put in bottom of casserole.
Add next 3 ingredients in layers.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: buzzy's vermouth scallops
directions: Marinate scallops in vermouth for several hours in the refrigerator.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet.
Add salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Add scallops and cook quickly over high heat, stirring occasionally, until golden brown (5 to 10 minutes).
Transfer to a heated platter.
To pan juices, add parsley, lemon juice and remaining butter.
Heat and pour over scallops.

title: fried zucchini or fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice zucchini or tomatoes about 1/2-inch thick.
Beat egg until frothy.
Dip slices into egg and then into flour.
Place about 1/2 inch of cooking oil in skillet and heat.
Place floured zucchini or tomatoes in skillet and cook on low heat until golden brown.
Place between paper plates to drain and to keep warm until all are fried.
Serves 2.

title: scalloped sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until just tender.
Peel and cut into crosswise slices.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Arrange half sweet potatoes in bottom, then 1/2 of the apple slices.
Sprinkle with half the mixture of salt, sugar and mace.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Repeat.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with 1 cup milk as directed on pack. Fold in whipped topping; stir 1 cup cookies and the
Rocks into pudding mixture. Spoon into pie crust. Sprinkle with remaining cookies. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on muffins.
Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: jamaican jerk ribs
directions: Mix all spices together and rub all surfaces of ribs.
Grill or roast in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked steak
directions: Dip steak into flour and then brown in oil.
Mix milk and soup together in a bowl.
Layer steak and soup in a casserole dish, putting remaining soup on top.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Place steak in oven for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Reserve juice.
Add juice and water to Jell-O to dissolve.
Remove from heat.
Blend in cranberry sauce until smooth.
Add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Blend in sour cream.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Chill.
Great served with turkey on Thanksgiving.

title: coconut delight
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 12 pan. Add flour and nuts. Press on bottom of pan to make crust. Bake at 350° until light brown. Let cool.

title: almond butter crunch wheels
directions: Line bottom and sides of an 8 or 9-inch cake pan with aluminum foil (not plastic wrap or wax paper).
Butter foil heavily.
Set aside.
Combine almonds, butter, sugar and corn syrup in 10-inch skillet.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil, stirring constantly, until mixture turns golden brown, about 5 or 6 minutes.
Working quickly, spread candy in prepared pan. Cool about 15 minutes or until firm.
Remove candy from pan by lifting edges of foil.
Peel off foil.
Cool thoroughly.
Candy may be presented as a gift wrapped disk or broken into pieces and placed in decorative jar or container.
Makes about 3/4 pound.

title: lo-cal punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake by directions, using skim milk, no oil and only 1 egg white.
Make pudding according to directions using skim milk. Let cake cool.

title: dolly's dutch ginger cookies
directions: Sieve flour and sugar together; add butter and knead together until a ball forms, then add cut up (small pieces) ginger.
Take 1/3 of the dough and put on a floured area.
Dolly uses a small glass; I use a bottom of a salad jar (Good Seasons).
Butter your baking sheet.
Set oven in the beginning of making, 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove at once from the baking sheet and put them on a rack to cool.

title: spicy mustard sauce
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar in a small bowl.
Cover and let stand at room temperature overnight.
Heat mustard, vinegar and sugar over low heat.
Whisk 1 tablespoon of mustard into beaten egg.
Return egg mixture to saucepan and simmer over low heat for 1 to 2 minutes, until slightly thickened.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Leave grease.
Add eggs and scramble with sausage.
Add milk and mix it thoroughly so the eggs are moist.
After milk is absorbed by the eggs, add the Cheez Whiz.
Mix it through real good until completely melted.
Heat clean skillet for tortillas just about 1 minute on each side to soften.
Put tortilla flat on plate.
Put mixture on tortilla. Add salsa (mild or hot).
Roll up and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake covered 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven; drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened.
Pour thickened sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese. Bake 5 minutes uncovered.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serve over crackers.

title: oven dinner rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In casserole, combine all ingredients.
Cover and bake 30 minutes or until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Fluff rice with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crabmeat cakes
directions: Combine milk and bread crumbs.
Gently stir in whites of hard-boiled eggs, finely sliced, and flaked crabmeat.
Blend in hard-boiled yolks, mashed.
Add mustard, pepper and melted butter. Form into three patties and roll in crushed Wheaties or bread crumbs.
Bake in 400° (hot) oven for 15 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk, ReaLime and food coloring.
Pour into pie shell and bake 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Cool and top with whipping cream.

title: cornflake crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces in double boiler, stir in peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat, add cereal, drop on wax paper.
Refrigerate until hardened.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and margarine.
Add next 5 ingredients. Mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center.
Pull up corners to top of chicken. Twist lightly and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, brush with butter and sprinkle with crouton crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: opera creams
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Knead mixture until it sticks together.
Form into small balls and place on cookie sheet and cool in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Melt chocolate and wax in top of double boiler.
Dip each balls in chocolate.
Place candy on wax paper.

title: citric acid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale (may be frozen until needed).
Add ginger ale and serve.
Makes 150 cups.
