title: apple dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling in cast-iron Dutch oven.
Dump cake mix over pie filling and put butter on top.

Put on campfire and cook until pie filling seeps to top of cake mix, then cover entire Dutch oven with coals and cook until crust is golden brown (about 10 minutes) or bake in oven at 350° in cake pan until done.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Dissolve soda in tomato soup and add to mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in loaf pan.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: "hurry 'n' wait" dinner
directions: Place the strips of uncooked bacon in bottom of a large skillet.
Cut round steak into finger lengths and arrange over bacon.
Top steak with thinly sliced onion.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange over the onion.
Place carrot pieces over the potatoes and top with the frozen limas.
Sprinkle each layer with seasonings.
Add tomatoes and water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
If family is late for dinner, simply add a little more water, reduce the heat and adjust.
Let the dinner "wait."
Serves 4.

title: brown rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour uncooked rice, margarine and both cans of soup into a covered dish.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan or large frying pan.
Stir in salt and flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens.
Add potatoes; heat with occasional stirring until sauce boils again.
Turn potatoes and sauce into a 9 x 13-inch glass or metal baking dish.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Add grated cheese to cover.
Place in oven which has been preheated to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour, or until the potatoes are tender.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: orange-broiled pork chops
directions: Place chops on unheated rack in broiler pan. Broil 4-inches from heat 10 minutes; turn and broil 5 minutes.

title: recipe for a happy life on earth
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrows and sympathy. Flavor with love and kindly advice.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith.
After pouring all of this into your daily life, bake with the heart of human kindness.
Serve with a smile anytime and it will satisfy the hunger of starved souls.

title: oyster chowder
directions: Drain oysters, reserving liquid.
Saute onion and celery in butter until tender in a Dutch oven.
Add milk, oyster liquid, corn, potato, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until heated.
Add oysters; simmer 5 minutes or until oyster edges curl.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Serves 8.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Stir together the baking mix, milk and cheese until a soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough from spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes at 450° or until lightly browned.
Mix butter, garlic powder and parsley and brush over warm biscuits before removing from the cookie sheet.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: baked bean dish
directions: Fry meat and add flour.
Season pork and beans with molasses to taste.
Mix together well and place in a casserole dish.
Cut bacon up into small pieces and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: In saucepan, heat milk, cottage cheese, honey and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
In a large bowl, combine warm liquid, whole wheat flour, 1 cup white flour and remaining ingredients. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour. Knead dough for about 2 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise.
Divide into 3 parts and put into greased loaf pans. Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cracker cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Fold beaten egg whites into cracker mixture. Place in cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls onto pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Rolls will not be very brown, but they will be done. Makes 7 to 8 rolls.
Recipe can be doubled easily.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and cocoa in saucepan or double boiler.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Gradually stir at least half of hot mixture into egg yolks that have been beaten.
Then blend into hot mixture in double boiler.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: gogo shake
directions: In a blender, blend banana until smooth.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add ice cream and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger vegetable casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, cook potato, onion and limas until tender. Mix together in casserole dish with can of Veg-All and soup; mix well.
Top with biscuits. Dot each biscuit with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake 20 minutes or until biscuits are browned.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Drain tofu and freeze for 48 hours.
Thaw and wrap tightly in cheesecloth, pressing to squeeze out liquid; crumble.
Combine red chili sauce, chili powder and tomato sauce in large saucepan. Blend in flour.
Add crumbled tofu and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through.

title: cheese 'n wiener crescents
directions: Slit wieners to within 1/2-inch of ends; insert strips of cheese.
Place wiener on shortest side of crescent dough triangles. Roll up individual wiener in single triangle.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: california salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to roaring boil.
Add cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Add onions, celery, shrimp and gelatine.
Mix together. Fold in mayonnaise.
Turn into a mold and chill for 8 hours.

title: cranberry crunch muffins
directions: Mix coarsely chopped cranberries, pecans and orange juice in large bowl.
Mix flour and baking powder in bowl.
Add to first mixture.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.
Makes 48 muffins.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and baking powder and set aside.
Mix the egg and oil until well blended.
Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients, stirring in gradually.
Fold in the blueberries and pour the batter into greased and floured muffin pans or pans lined with cupcake papers.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Use 1/2 cup batter for each waffle.
Bake on hot waffle iron until golden brown.

title: quick microwave lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add sauce and water.
Spread 1/3 mixture onto lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch microwavable dish. Put 4 uncooked noodles on sauce.
Layer 1 cup cottage cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese over noodles.
Top with 4 noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese (1 cup each).
Then add remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap with a small corner uncovered to steam.
Microwave at Medium for 32 to 35 minutes.
Turn after 15 minutes.
Uncover after 35 minutes and sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and microwave on Medium for 2 minutes.

title: apple tea
directions: Heat ingredients in crock-pot until red hots dissolve.

title: mexi-cali pinwheels
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: christmas gems
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in midget paper cups in muffin tins.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour carefully.
Spoon into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until it tests done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place skinned chicken pieces in large casserole dish (12 x 14-inch).
Bring to boil cream of chicken soup and chicken broth and pour over chicken.
Mix together flour, oleo and buttermilk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 40 minutes or until brown.

title: potatoes stuffed with turkey ham
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes, then pat dry.
Use a fork to prick the potatoes.
Place on a microwave-proof plate and cover with plastic wrap.
Vent the wrap by pulling back a small corner.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 5 minutes.
Rotate the plate a half turn, then cook on High for 5 to 7 minutes more or until the potatoes are tender.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Cut each potato lengthwise in half.
Scoop out the pulp, leaving 1/4-inch thick shells.
Set the shells aside.
In bowl, mash potato pulp. Stir in yogurt and blend well.
Stir in turkey ham, onions, green peppers and black pepper.
Pile the mixture into potato shell. Transfer shells to a platter.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Vent the wrap.
Cook in microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes until heated through.
Serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam (not aluminum).
Put 2 pounds of potatoes on bottom.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and 1/2 pound of bacon, crumbled.
Repeat layers, potatoes, salt and bacon.
Pour whipping cream over.
Cover with tinfoil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour the next day.

title: gone all-day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water/wine and flour until smooth; combine with remaining ingredients in a covered roasting pan .
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: coconut cherry bars
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar gradually.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
In a small bowl, mix four, baking powder and salt.
Stir dry ingredients into cream mixture.
Add nuts, cherries and semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Spread dough into greased 10x15 inch pan.
Bake at 375 for about 25 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into bars.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Soften tortillas in chicken stock. Line pan with tortillas.
Layer chicken, soups, cheese and tomatoes.
On top, add more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Strain or squeeze grated potatoes in cheesecloth to remove excess water.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in melted fat and then stir in flour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Break spaghetti in small pieces.
Cook; rinse in cold water. Mix all ingredients with salad dressing and chill overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables.
Grease casserole with butter.
Place a layer of asparagus, layer of beans, layer of peas and sliced water chestnuts.
Pour undiluted cream of mushroom soup over vegetables. Spread mushrooms over soup.
Grate cheese and place over everything.
Melt butter and toss bread crumbs in it.
Spread over cheese.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust browns.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Beat eggs to blend.
Add oil, sugar, molasses and vanilla. Continue beating until thick and foamy.
Combine dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Beat until just blended.
Add zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Mix gently.
Makes 24 muffins.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chow chow(mildred gregory)
directions: Cook everything separately except corn and peppers which may be put in raw.
To 6 quarts of chow chow, take vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric.
Cook 5 minutes.
Can hot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the first four ingredients and beaten eggs. Add vanilla.
Add the rest of the dry ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Roll into small balls.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, then add other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into mold or container and chill overnight.

title: butter brittle
directions: In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, stir together the sugar, water and corn syrup.
Over medium heat, stirring constantly, bring to a boil. Add peanuts gradually so mixture continues to boil.
Cook, stirring often, to 260° on a candy thermometer or until a teaspoon of mixture dropped in a cup of cold water forms a ball that is plastic but hard enough to hold its shape.
Add butter and stir until it melts.

Continue cooking, stirring often, to 300° or until a teaspoon dropped into cold water separates into hard brittle threads. Remove from heat. Quickly stir in baking soda. Pour onto 2 ungreased cookie sheets.
Spread with a spatula. When cold, break into pieces.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: cream cheese peach pie
directions: Mix together.
Spoon mixture in dish.
Spread evenly with spoon.

title: hobo bread
directions: Put raisins in a large pot that has a tight fitting lid.
Pour in boiling water to cover.
Stir in baking soda.
Cover tightly and let stand overnight.

title: sunshine casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes or until set.

title: sweet and sour brussels sprouts
directions: Drain cooked
Brussels sprouts.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble. Combine vinegar, sugar and seasonings.
Stir into sprouts. Sprinkle bacon over top.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Add 1/2 of poppy seed.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle with chicken and add rest of mixture.
Melt margarine and add crackers and poppy seed. Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: shane's meat loaf italiano
directions: Take off sausage skin and mix well with ground beef and all other ingredients.
Form into a loaf.
Mozzarella cheese can be sprinkled on top, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spiced orange cranberry sauce
directions: Wash and stem cranberries.
Use blender to liquify oranges and lemon, which has been seeded.
Put cranberries, orange, lemon and water in heavy pot.
Bring to a boil and cook until cranberries begin to pop, stirring constantly.
Add sugar and spices; bring back to a boil, stirring constantly.
Jar and seal.

title: bavarian chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion soup mix.
Pour into a well buttered 9 x 15-inch glass dish.
Place chicken on top of mix, bone side down.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Don't peek or lift foil! Enjoy!!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, peanut butter and sugar well.
Stir in Cool Whip and vanilla.
Place mixture in graham cracker pie crust. Good!

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat for 10 minutes; drain.
Add sauce, water and salt; blend well.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook lasagna according to package directions; drain well.
Combine cottage cheese and egg.
Spread 3/4 cup meat sauce on bottom of greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Arrange a layer of lasagna over sauce.
Top with layers of cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce. Repeat layers twice, ending with a layer of lasagna.
Spread meat sauce over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Combine half and half and instant pudding.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add crushed or chopped candy bars. Add to graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion and salt and shape into 50 to 60 meatballs.
Brown.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large skillet; heat, stirring constantly, over low heat until smooth. Add meatballs and simmer for 1 hour.

title: creamy orange spread
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; beat well.
Cover; refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve with vanilla wafers, graham crackers or chocolate wafers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake sheet cake according to directions on box, using either 2 eggs or 3 egg whites.
Let cake cool and poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour cream of coconut in holes.
If you like, mix Eagle Brand milk with cream of coconut and pour in holes.
Spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Sprinkle shredded coconut on top of Cool Whip.

title: baked pork chops in mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms and pepper in butter until soft.
Drain butter.
Add wine, tomato sauce and seasonings; cook until the sauce turns brown.

title: grammy's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs in bowl. Add flour, sugar, honey and salt to taste. Add corn and milk.
Dot with butter. Bake in pan of water at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add bell pepper, onion, celery, salt, pepper, soup and tomatoes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Prepare 9-inch baked pie shell as directed on package.
Cool. Mash enough berries to measure 1 cup.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water and crushed berries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in few drops red food color; cool.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; spread on bottom of cooled baked pie shell.
Fill shell with remaining berries.
Pour berry mixture over top.
Chill at least 3 hours or until set.

title: pizza rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Brown 'N Serve rolls.
Cut Brown 'N Serve rolls into half and pinch out centers and add half of the centers to the mixture and mix well.
Then fill centers of the rolls with the mixture.
Then bake as usual until rolls are brown. Then put others together and put back in package in freezer.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour or less at 325°.
Makes 1 loaf. Recipe can be doubled and freezes good.

title: easy  chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding according to box directions.
Pour pudding mix into 8-inch baked pie shell. Refrigerate. When set, top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and serve. Serves 8.

title: bubbling recipe(for making bubbles; not edible)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Place cover on and shake. Let settle for 4 hours before using.
Store, covered, in refrigerator to extend suds shelf life, then allow to warm before using.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil, drain and cool squash.
Add carrot, pimento, soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: squash rolls
directions: Scald the milk in double boiler. Add butter; let cool. Then add salt, sugar and squash. In separate bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.

Mix yeast with other ingredients, adding 6 cups of flour or until you get the right consistency. Knead and cover; let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour). Roll out dough. Cut and arrange in buttered 10-inch pans.
Brush with melted butter. Cover with cloth. Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Put all vegetables in a bowl.
Add 1/2 tablespoon seasoned salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with Zesty Italian.
Cover bowl; refrigerate about 3 hours.
Lasts a long time!! Serves 10 to 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together ingredients and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until done.

title: mixed bean barbecue
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook lima beans without salt in 1 cup boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain limas.
Combine in greased 2 1/2-quart deep casserole with kidney beans, pork and beans, soup mix, chili sauce, molasses, mustard, Tabasco and about 3/4 of frank pieces.
Line edge of casserole with rest of frankfurters. Bake about 50 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: clam fritter
directions: Drain Clams and chop.
Sift all dry ingredients together. Combine Eggs, Milk, Onion, Butter and Clams, pour into dry ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot fat (350 degrees).
Fry about three minutes or until golden brown.
Drain.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan greased with margarine.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over this mixture.
Cool and cut into pieces.
Freeze.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Layer tortilla shell, chicken, peppers, onions and cheese in a casserole dish. Combine soup, RoTel tomatoes and chicken broth and pour over layered ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and refried beans and mix thoroughly.
Spread mixture in deep 3-quart casserole.
Layer remaining ingredients (omitting taco chips) in order listed.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until hot and bubbly. Serve with taco chips.

title: cheese-stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut off ends of squash.
Boil whole for approximately 12 minutes until barely tender.
Remove from water.
Slice lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp and invert on paper towel to drain. Combine all other ingredients, except crackers and butter.
Stuff zucchini shells.

title: cajun red beans
directions: Cook pinto beans as directed.
When they get tender, add tomatoes, onion, bell pepper and garlic with thyme, oregano, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce and green onion.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add sausage and salt.
Cook until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat peach juice and margarine together.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Add to juice and margarine that is in baking dish. Sprinkle peaches over top.
Do not stir!
Sprinkle top of peaches with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° until golden brown.

title: grape-grapefruit punch
directions: Thaw concentrate.
Combine with grapefruit juice and chill. Just before serving, stir in carbonated water with up and down motion.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired.

title: *marinated carrots or copper pennies
directions: Cook, cool and drain carrots.
After carrots cool, mix in other ingredients and refrigerate.
Make the night before using for best results.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make a paste of red food coloring and cocoa. Cream thoroughly the shortening and sugar. Add paste to that. Add buttermilk, alternately with cake flour and salt. Beat well after each addition. Then add vanilla. Put soda in vinegar. Fold soda and vinegar. Mix into batter. Bake in two 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and split each layer in two.

title: carbonara
directions: Brown bacon in oil 7 to 8 minutes. Cover to keep warm. Add salted water and cook pasta as directed. Stir often. (Save 1/3 cup pasta water for additional moisture if needed.) Beat eggs. Add to cheese and add garlic. Combine drained pasta, egg/cheese mixture, bacon, salt and pepper. The warm bacon and pasta will cook the egg mixture.

title: yeast rise dumplings(from the kitchen of lola zahn)
directions: Dissolve 1 package yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, parsley, onions and egg.
Add flour.
Stir.
Let rise until double in size.
Drop by spoonfuls onto gently boiling stew. Allow batter to rest on meat and vegetables.
Cover tightly and steam 20 minutes.
Do not lift lid.

title: pasta salad trivoli
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Italian dressing, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add chicken, cheese and vegetables to cooked pasta.
Toss lightly to mix.
Add mayonnaise mixture and toss to mix.
Chill 6 hours or more.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Butter a deep baking dish.
Then start at the bottom and arrange in layers.
First potatoes, then the ground beef, onions, green pepper if used, uncooked rice and tomatoes.
Season each layer, cover and bake for 2 hours at 300°.
Parmesan cheese may be used on top.

title: cheese and herb flatbread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the cup of warm water.
In a bowl, combine flour and salt.
Add dissolved yeast.
Knead by hand until smooth. (If dough is sticky, gradually add up to 1/2 cup flour.)
Place in a bowl greased with safflower margarine.
Turn dough once to coat.
Cover and let rise in a warm place 1 1/2 hours or until double in size.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Mix well.
Shape into sticks and roll in chili powder.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Mix together vanilla wafers and 1 1/2 sticks melted margarine; press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (save some for topping). Beat cream cheese, 1/2 cup margarine and sugar.
Spread on pressed crumbs.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries and juice.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
When slightly set, spread Cool Whip on top and refrigerate.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: hawaiian cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well in order listed.
Serves 10.

title: our favorite tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as per instructions on box.
Drain tuna.
Combine prepared macaroni and cheese with tuna and cream of celery soup (straight out of the can).
Transfer mixture into large baking dish; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until you can see the middle bubbling.

title: company chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Reserve one cup of broth.
Cool and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix together soup, sour cream, broth and wine to make a sauce.
Add chicken, broccoli and mushrooms.
Place in shallow baking dish and top with cheese first and then with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes or until bread crumbs are brown.
Serve with rice or pasta.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces and sprinkle generously with garlic and onion salt.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cook 2 hours in electric skillet, adding sauce as needed or bake in 350° oven until done.
Can use a crock-pot but allow 7 to 8 hours for cooking.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into one large ball or two small balls.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with nuts.

title: turtles
directions: Unwrap caramels.
Arrange 6 at a time in a circle on a buttered plate.
Microwave on High 30 to 40 seconds until soft. Remove to cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil.
Use 1 pecan half for head and 4 pieces for the legs.
Press into caramels. Place kisses in a 4-cup glass bowl; microwave on Medium 5 minutes. Stir in paraffin until melted.
Spoon over turtles, leaving tips showing.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 18.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of large pan.
Spread chili on top of cheese.
Top with Cheddar.
Top with jalapenos to taste. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or hot and bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bubble bath
directions: Stir together dishwashing liquid, epsom salt and glycerine. Add perfume and food coloring, if desired.
Store in tightly covered bottle or jar.
Shake container before adding 1 to 2 tablespoons to running bath water.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll out on floured surface and cut biscuits. Place on buttered pan. Bake at 350° till golden brown.

title: fried oysters with diablo sauce
directions: Drain oysters in strainer or colander.
Divide among 1 or 2 flat pans and season with the seasoning.
Mix thoroughly.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Put flour into sheet pan and season with the salt, paprika and white pepper.
Dust oysters in flour and lay out closely together on sheet pan.
Using small portions of fat, spread generously onto hot grill.
Toss 1/8 of floured oysters onto grill at a time from sheet pans and cook until golden brown. Drain.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Make in one-inch balls. Roll in flour and put in baking pan.
Pour milk over the meatballs to cover bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn and bake 30 minutes more.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Mix pizza crust mix as directed.
Spread in pizza pan. Scramble eggs (do not let them cook completely done).
Fry bacon. Layer eggs and crumbled bacon.
Mix cheeses together and spread over pizza.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: grandmother robertson's tea cakes
directions: Mix up to a stiff batter; divide dough.
Roll out each half on a towel.
Cut out with biscuit cutter.
Grease pan.
Cook in oven at 425° or 475° until done.

title: ladyfinger delight
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In another bowl, beat cream until stiff.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.

title: fudge filled peanut butter bar cookies
directions: Combine the cake mix, peanut butter, 1/2 cup butter and eggs. Mix until the dough holds together.
Press 2/3 of the dough into the bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Reserve the remaining dough for topping

title: marilyn rouse's spoon rolls
directions: Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Cut in Crisco.
Add 2 packages of yeast to warm water, then add beaten egg to yeast water.
Mix wet and dry ingredients until well blended.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 18 to 20 rolls.
Serve warm.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Combine egg, milk, flour and salt.
Dip onions in batter.
Fry in hot shortening.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Sprinkle with salt. Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach; dry well, then chop. Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Mix well. Roll into small balls (about 1 1/2 inches). Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Can also be frozen before baking. Makes 4 dozen.

title: egg custard
directions: Boil milk, sugar and butter.
Beat eggs with reserved milk and add vanilla.
Pour hot mixture in egg mixture, beating constantly. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake for 45 minutes or until firm at 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat again until stiff.
Put on pie and brown in a 350° oven.

title: scalloped succotash
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add water to corn liquid, if necessary, to make 3/4 cup.
In bowl, combine corn liquid, corn, limas, evaporated milk, cheese, eggs, onion, pimiento, pepper and 1 1/2 cups of cracker crumbs.
Turn into a 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Place one package of rolls in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, clear to edge.
Mix cream cheese, egg and sugar and spread over rolls.
Place second package of rolls over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: crab cheese spread
directions: Cover serving platter with 1 inch layer of cream cheese, soften if necessary.
Mix crab meat with cocktail sauce and spread over top and sides of cream cheese.
Serve on crackers.

title: oven beef roast
directions: On large sheet of foil, place roast, which has been rinsed and wiped with paper towel.
Over roast, spread the mushroom soup. Sprinkle on dry onion soup mix.
Salt sparingly, then pepper. Close foil tightly and bake in 325° oven for about 3 hours.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: "bundles" of green beans
directions: Drain beans, dividing into individual servings.
Wrap each bundle with 1/2 slice uncooked bacon.
Place in a baking dish. Mix other ingredients; pour over beans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
16 bundles.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the first 3 ingredients.
Let cool.
When cool, add sugar, flour and salt. Beat well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 12 x 16-inch pan or two smaller pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: calzones
directions: Such as:
Mozzarella cheese, ground beef, chicken, pepperoni, broccoli, bell pepper and onions; anything!

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour over shrimp that have been shelled and deveined.
Marinate 2 hours.
Cook over hot grill 10 minutes or until shrimp are pink.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour and seasonings; gradually add milk. Cook slowly until thickened.
Add 1 cup cheese.
Stir until melted.
Place broccoli in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Cover with chicken and sauce and top with crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Mix until smooth.
Chill 1 or 2 hours before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box for 3-layer cake.
Bake and cool completely.

Mix sugar and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil and let simmer 10 minutes; add pina colada drink mix and let cool. Stack cake with pina colada mixture, then cool whip and coconut until all layers are stacked. When all are stacked, frost outside of cake with cool whip, sprinkle with coconut.
Decorate with cherries. Refrigerate before serving. You will also want to refrigerate all leftovers.

title: easy sticky rolls
directions: Combine 1 tablespoon melted margarine, brown sugar, nuts and water in bottom of 8-inch round, glass pie plate, spreading mixture evenly in bottom of pan.

title: grilled bass
directions: Melt butter.
Add pepper, garlic, salt and lemon juice.
Cook fish on grill in fish rack.
Baste hot side with butter mixture.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread beans onto a serving plate.
Cream the next 3 ingredients together and spread onto beans.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve with nacho chips.

title: carrot marmalade
directions: Mix ingredients and boil slowly until quite thick. Watch so it doesn't burn. Remove and add 1/2 pack of Certo and mix thoroughly. Fill 3 jelly jars and refrigerate.

title: tuna tulips
directions: Make biscuit dough and roll out into squares or use canned biscuits.
Put dough squares into greased muffin tins.
Combine all other ingredients and divide equally into each dough square. Overlap corners of dough.
Bake in a 400° oven about 30 minutes. Makes 10 to 12.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients together using as many peppers as desired. Bake at 400° for about 40 to 45 minutes in an oblong cake pan.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie plate.
Slice apples; fill pie plate (2/3 full).
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top over layers of apples (set aside).
Melt butter or margarine and beat egg.
Add the chopped walnuts, 1 cup sugar and flour together. Mix with butter or margarine and egg; spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Place raisins and water in pan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Set aside.
Do not drain!
Mix flour with baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
In separate bowl, cream shortening. Gradually add sugar; beat well by hand.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in raisins with liquid; mix well.
Gradually add flour mixture, blending thoroughly after each addition.
Drop from tablespoon about 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: green rice
directions: Cook peas.
Combine onions, soup and rice.
Stir in peas. Place in greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken vegetable rice
directions: Heat margarine in a large deep skillet.
Cook chicken until browned.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Add onion and pepper.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Bring first 2 ingredients to a boil.
Blend in peanut butter, then add Rice Krispies.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: christmas strawberry cookies
directions: In skillet, combine dates, coconut, sugar, oleo, egg and salt. Cook, stirring over medium heat, until mixture thickens and bubbles (5 to 10 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes; form into balls. Keep fingers moist.

title: kielbasi roll-ups
directions: Cut kielbasi in pieces to fit across cooked lasagna noodles. Make a slit lengthwise in kielbasi pieces.
Put kielbasi on cooked noodle and fill slit with shredded cheese.
Wrap up in noodle. Lay in casserole dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over roll-ups.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Fold in crushed pineapple.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs and oil; beat well. Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Beat in zucchini. Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: salmon loaf with tomato-dill sauce
directions: Flake salmon; discarding skin and bones.
In medium mixing bowl, combine egg and milk, then stir in bread crumbs, green onion, dill weed and dry mustard.
Add flaked salmon and mix thoroughly.

title: nothin' soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a boil. Turn down heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Almost zero calories!

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together corn, sugar, flour and salt and pepper to taste in a large casserole dish.
Next, add eggs, milk, butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, until slightly brown on top.

title: church window candy
directions: In a saucepan, combine the chocolate chips and the butter. Cook and stir over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in marshmallows and 1/4 cup nuts.
Divide in half. Shape each half into a 6-inch long log and roll each log in the remaining nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper or clear plastic wrap and chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Store, covered, in the refrigerator.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Mix sugar and flour with juice and blend well.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: kid's free form pretzels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, salt and cheese to make a stiff dough (add more flour, if needed).
Knead for 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll out like pencils (when you roll, make your hands light like a feather) and shape as a pretzel or make the alphabet or whatever your imagination comes up with.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Mix in soup, milk and 1/2 of grated cheese (reserving the rest for the top).
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with the reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour kabobs
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in boiling water for 8 minutes; drain. Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Cut slices in quarters and set aside.

title: mexican hash
directions: Brown onions and peppers in a pan. Add hamburger and brown lightly. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday and party sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and place in a 4-quart Dutch oven and cover with water.
Cover and cook over medium heat.
Meanwhile, drain juice from pineapple.
Place juice in a heavy saucepan over medium heat. Add cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, raisins, lemon and orange slices. Add brown sugar and butter.
Stir to blend ingredients thoroughly.
Lower heat; cover and cook until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove orange and lemon slices.
When potatoes are done, pour off water.
Let potatoes cool.
When cool, peel and slice them, then cover bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Pour some spiced juice over potatoes.
Add remaining sweet potatoes, mandarin orange segments, pineapple chunks and bananas.
Pour remaining spiced juice and raisins on top.
Top with pecans.
Sprinkle on miniature marshmallows.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until marshmallows melt and turn golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix together coconut and chopped nuts.
Spread evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions, then pour over coconut and nuts.
Beat together margarine and cream cheese; beat in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Dab on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into rolls and wrap in wax paper; chill overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a heavy skillet over medium heat, saute salt pork approximately 10 minutes or until crisp and brown. Drain and reserve fat.
You now have cracklins.

title: pepper steak
directions: While frozen, slice meat as thin as possible.
Put 3 tablespoons cornstarch and mix with soy sauce until a little thicker than milk.
Dump meat into mixture and cover meat.
Put 2 tablespoons oil into frying pan.
Put in meat and brown.
Take out meat and put in onions and pepper.
Cook until crunchy but soft. Put meat back.
Add water to remainder of soy mixture.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ham. Lay ham flat on cookie sheet or wax paper. Spread mixture on ham and roll up. Place in freezer for 10 minutes. Remove and cut into 1/2-inch rolls. Serve.

title: crunchy potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes and prick all over with a fork.
Bake in preheated oven 1 hour, until just tender.
Remove potatoes from oven and increase heat to 425°.

title: wedding punch
directions: Pour water over tea.
Let steep 3 minutes, then strain. Dissolve sugar in lemon juice
and
add to tea.
Mix all other ingredients.
Chill with crushed ice.
Delicious party punch.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the cream cheese with the sugar until fluffy.
Fold in peanut butter and mix well, then fold in the Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell and cool.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, oil, sour cream and eggs.
Pour half of batter in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Pour over cake batter in pan and swirl.
Then add rest of the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: coconut cream pie(one pie)
directions: Combine egg yolks, salt and milk.
Stir over medium heat until warm.
Combine sugar and flour, mixing well.
Gradually add milk to mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Remove from heat and pour into one pie shell.
Chill.

title: hot, spiced russian tea
directions: Place water, cinnamon and cloves in gallon pot and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add tea bags and steep for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add sugar and fruit juices.
Serve hot.

title: breast of chicken marsala
directions: Mix flour with pepper and paprika and lightly dust the chicken breasts.
Melt butter in hot skillet; saute chicken gently over low heat, until golden on both sides and juices run clear.
Remove to a platter and keep warm in a 200° oven.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery in bowl.
Mix salad dressing, onion salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and celery; mix.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serves 3 only.

title: banana nut bread(2 loaves)
directions: Cream butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add bananas and sour cream.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
May be served immediately or refrigerated.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine and pour into eggs.
Beat this and add cottage cheese.
Add cornbread mix, broccoli and onion.
Pour into greased skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: mud cake
directions: Mix cookies, chocolate pudding and milk.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, 1/4 cup margarine and powdered sugar.
Put 10 ounces of cookie crumbs on top.
Can use a flowerpot and gummy worms.

title: sweet refrigerator pickles
directions: Select young firm cucumbers.
Slice into even slices.
Place in a large bowl.
Bring vinegar, sugar, spices and salt to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Immediately pour over cucumbers.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Cover and cool.
Refrigerate 1 week before using. Pickles may also be processed if you wish to keep them longer but they will keep a long time in the refrigerator.
Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: easy asian lettuce or tortilla wraps
directions: Mix dressing, peanut butter, chili/cayenne powder and ginger. Pour sesame oil to a nonstick skillet.
Add chicken, nuts and half of dressing mixture.
Saute over medium heat until hot.
Remove to a serving bowl.
In a separate bowl, toss coleslaw mix, bell pepper and cilantro.

title: dump cake(method:  dutch oven)
directions: For easy cleaning, line Dutch oven with foil.
Place in Dutch oven the peaches with juice.
Dump over top of peaches the cake mix; spread evenly.
Stir enough to moisten cake mix; dot top with the butter or margarine.
Place lid on Dutch oven.
Place coals on top and bottom of Dutch oven; bake for 45 minutes.

title: quick pre-school snack
directions: Simply have children frost their own cookies.
Decorate with sprinkles.
Quick, fun and easy!

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together by hand, oil, nuts, apples, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Sift together soda and flour.
Add to apple mixture. Bake in an ungreased angel food pan for about 75 minutes at 350°.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage coarse and boil in salted water for 8 minutes; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and blend. Gradually add milk and stir in cheese.
Stir until thick and smooth.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Alternate cabbage and sauce in casserole.
Top with croutons and bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: maple stuffed sweet potato
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake potatoes 50 to 60 minutes or until easily pierced with a fork.
Remove from oven and cool slightly. Slice potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving
a 1/2-inch thick shell.
Place shells in 13 x 9-inch pan and transfer pulp to a food processor or blender.
Add remaining ingredients and process or blend until smooth.
Spoon mixture evenly into shells.
Return to oven and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer, until heated.
Especially good at Thanksgiving.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and it's ready to eat.

title: sicilian lasagna
directions: Wash chickens well and remove livers, gizzards and hearts. Split chickens in half, cutting through backs and center breasts. Place halved pieces in a large roasting pan, with wings and legs sides up.
Pour Italian dressing over the chicken.
Use both bottles.

title: baked salmon steaks
directions: Line dish
with
foil; pour in the milk and flour.
Lay in the salmon
steaks.
Add
the seasoning, then dot the fish with butter and grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Put
ingredients
in a saucepan (sugar, water, cinnamon and butter): set on low heat until butter melts.
Do not boil! Slice 6 apples; peel and cut into slices.
Place apples in the cinnamon mixture.
Leave
on
burner
while
you
fix biscuit mixture.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown onions; add remaining ingredients, except green beans and cheese.
Cook until bubbly; don't boil, just simmer.
Toss together with green beans; put into a baking dish.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: turkey fettuccini marinara
directions: Cook fettuccini; drain.
Set aside.
Using nonstick skillet with cooking spray, cook turkey breasts 1 1/2 to 2 minutes per side or until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet; keep warm. Add olive oil, mushrooms, onion, pepper and thyme.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in fettuccini. Remove from heat; keep warm.

title: chinese clusters
directions: Place chocolate and butterscotch chips in 1 1/2 to 2 quart mixing bowl.
Heat in microwave on cookmatic level 6 for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Let set until firm.

title: polenta
directions: Bring water and 1 tsp. salt to boiling - Gradually stir in polenta.
Simmer gently, stir frequently to prevent sticking for about 30 minutes until mixture is very thick, (use wooden spoon). Stir in butter.
Spoon from pan into buttered bowl, let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Invert onto flat plate - Traditionally you cut slices with a tautly held string.
Cut into thick slices and serve hot topped with Spaghetti sauce or butter and cheese (Parmesan, Romano, Fontina, Jack).
You can chill Polenta and slice cold in 3/4 inch thick and fry in olive oil or grill - serve with sauce or buttered with cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Boil water; set off heat.
Add Jell-O and salt; stir until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to chilled mixture and stir well.

title: pasty pie
directions: Everyone knows the recipe for pasties, meat, potatoes and onions, sliced thin, and a good crust.
Here are a few hints that Margaret passed on to me.
First, she combined pork and beef. Secondly, she had her potatoes and onions sliced paper thin. Third, she layered first the potatoes, then the onions and placed the meat on top.
By doing this, the juices from the meat was absorbed by the vegetables.
The last few years, she was unable to stand long enough to make individual pasties so she reached for an 8 or 8 3/4-inch pie pan and made it in one large pie.
It worked, and we have followed her recipe for pasty pie.
Believe me, a good sized wedge of pasty pie is hearty eating.

title: the old warehouse rum pudding recipe
directions: Combine dry ingredients, egg yolks and half and half.
Put in double boiler.
Heat until gelatine dissolves (foamy).
Set pan in ice.
Add the rum.
Add orange rind to taste.
Stir occasionally. When it sets up, take off at once! Beat egg whites and 2/3 cup additional sugar; fold gelatine mixture in.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon.
Stir Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar or lemon juice together.
Pour over broccoli and mix together.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients; put on a slow fire until sugar has melted. Then cook for 25 minutes.

title: tuna fish sandwich spread
directions: Cover tuna with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain well to get excess fat and water from tuna.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: tasty rice
directions: Melt butter; add converted rice until it is golden brown.
Add the mushrooms; mix water with onion soup mix and add to rice. Bring to a boil. Let simmer on low for 1/2 hour covered, stirring occasionally.
Makes a nice side dish.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of electric mixer for 1 minute; add sugar and lemon juice, beating well. Add soda, salt and spices. Fold in flour and pumpkin until well combined. Spread batter onto a greased cookie sheet or jelly roll pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Turn cake out onto a towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar and roll up, jelly roll fashion. Let cool. When cake is cooled, unroll and spread with filling. Re-roll filled cake, wrap in foil and store in the refrigerator until serving time.

title: cousin mary's lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the first three ingredients.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches or 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients about 3 minutes or until
light and fluffy. Pour over hot crust.
Bake about 25 minutes longer.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yields 16 cookies.

title: gruyere-stuffed potatoes with sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scrub potatoes and pat dry.
Brush in the oil.
Bake until tender, about 1 hour.
Seal in paper bag and let stand 15 minutes.
Cut 3/4-inch thick horizontal slice from top of each potato.
Scoop pulp from potatoes into bowl reserving shells; mash pulp using masher or mixer.
Add rest of ingredients and mix until fluffy.
Spoon into shells.
(Can be prepared one day ahead and chilled; bring to room temperature before continuing.)

title: surprise meatball kabobs
directions: Soak four 8-inch bamboo skewers in water 10 minutes. Meanwhile combine the ground beef, egg, chili powder, garlic salt and oregano.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Divide mixture into 12 equal portions.
Form each portion around a ripe olive.
Thread 3 meatballs alternately with 2 zucchini pieces on each skewer. Lightly greased unheated grid.

Place meatballs kabobs on grid over medium-low coals. Grill 12 to 15 minutes until done, turning and brushing with barbecue sauce occasionally. Add a cherry tomato to the end of each skewer after cooking.
Yields 4 kabobs.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain. Add pickle juice, then pickles, onion and mayonnaise. Mix well and chill.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Bake chicken.
Cool and
remove from bones.
Add oil in skillet, then combine onion, celery and bell pepper.
Let cook about 5 minutes.
Then
add
soup, cheese and Ro-Tel.
Combine chicken, rice and
mixture in baking dish.	Bake at 300° about 30 minutes.
Season
chicken
and rice with salt and pepper to taste while cooking separately.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix salt, flour and eggs together with fork.
Make well in mixture and add water.
Stir until consistency is like pie crust. Add additional water if needed.
Roll out dough and cut into strips.
Add noodles to boiling chicken or beef broth and cook until done.

title: angel cookies
directions: Add ingredients as given.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into balls and press down with a fork.
Bake at 350°.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add remaining ingredients.

title: that incredible holiday sandwich
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Hollow out both sides.
Spread mayonnaise and cream cheese evenly on both sides.
Sprinkle both sides with chopped onion.
Sprinkle both sides liberally with chopped parsley.
Drain dill quarters and wrap with two slices boiled ham (I use rectangular size slices).
Place pickle and ham roll diagonally across trough in one side of bread loaf.
Cut last pickle and ham roll in two to fill space at ends of loaf.
Place top of loaf over filled bottom loaf and press down gently.
Wrap tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate for several hours before serving.
Cut slices at angle, about 1 1/2 inches thick to serve.

title: polish meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 2-pound loaf tin with the butter.
Set aside.
Put all the ingredients in a large mixing bowl; stir to blend them thoroughly.
Spoon the mixture into a loaf tin.
Place the tin in a large tin, half filled with cold water. Place the tin in the center of the oven; bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, or until the meat loaf has shrunk away from the sides of the tin.
After removing from oven, leave this meat loaf in the tin for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cooled slightly.
Pour off any fat.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake sheet cake according to directions on package.
Combine cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour mixture over hot cake.
Spread whipped topping over cooled cake and sprinkle with coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Flavor improves after chilling for 24 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of loaf pans.
Mix Crisco and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix in chopped nuts and raisins.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
Remove from pan and cool completely before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans or 3 loaves in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans.

title: lutefisk grot(lutefisk pudding)
directions: Scald rice; then cook in milk until thick.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a buttered baking dish.
If too thick, add a bit more scalded milk.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and bake in a moderate 350° oven about 1 hour, give or take.

title: coconut poppy seed cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, adding poppy seeds and coconut extract if desired to batter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding mix on low speed for 2 minutes.
Spread over the cake.
Spread with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with coconut if desired.
Yield:
20 to 24 servings.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Marinate overnight and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be kept warm in crock-pot on low temperature.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except broth.
Add boiled broth. Pour into 12 hole muffin pan, 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Measure flour.
Add sugar.
In a saucepan, put oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add eggs; beat.
Add buttermilk to which is added soda and salt.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes with mixer.
Add next three ingredients to the beaten eggs.
In a separate bowl mix together baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture and beat.
Pour onto greased and floured jelly roll pan and top with chopped walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Invert and roll, (hot) in a thin dish towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, cool.

title: mock lasagna(crock-pot)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Place in pot and add all ingredients, except noodles and oil.
Stir thoroughly.
Cook noodles just until tender; drain and toss in oil.
Place in pot and fold in cheese and meat mixture.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: Boil for 20 minutes the green beans, garlic and salt.
Cook until thick the butter, flour, milk, salt and chili powder.
Layer drained beans, mushrooms, almonds and sliced cheese.
Cover with half of the sauce.
Repeat until all used.
Top with Post Toasties or bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: explorer bacon
directions: Put two layers of paper towels on the plate.
Put bacon in rows on the paper towels.
Cover bacon slices with another paper towel.
Microwave on High for 1 minute for each slice.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add milk, flour, baking soda and salt.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan and top with fruit.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza pasta salad(this salad is good for barbecue time.)
directions: Combine rotini, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, green onions, and pepperoni.
In smaller bowl combine Parmesan cheese, vinegar, oil and seasonings; mix dressing with rotini mixture cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add croutons before serving.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse and drain lentils; in large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes.
Contains 2 grams fat, 0 mg cholesterol.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions.
Drain and toss with 2 tablespoons butter.
Put half of macaroni in sprayed 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cover with slices of American cheese.
Top evenly with remaining macaroni, then another layer of cheese slices.
Stir together milk and 2 tablespoons butter until melted.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, then cover loosely with foil to prevent a hard crust on top.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes more until liquid is no longer "runny" in bottom.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Mix jello, nuts, coconut and milk together.
Chill until stiff.
Roll into small balls, roll balls into last box of jello and put into a plate.
Add plastic stems.

title: moms best pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 15 inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: quick hollandaise
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pan.
Heat slowly stirring constantly until hot.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: aloha cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cream together cream cheese and milk.
Add dry pudding.
Pour over cooled cake.
Add pineapple to Cool Whip; mix well.
Place on top of pudding mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut and crushed walnuts.

title: cheesy beef pie
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Sprinkle meat with cornstarch; blend in.
Stir in parsley, mushrooms and enchilada sauce.
Unroll 1 package of rolls and place the 4 sections of dough together, forming a 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Seal edges together.
Roll into a 12-inch square.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate; trim edge even with plate.
Separate one of the eggs; set yolk aside.
Beat egg white with remaining 2 eggs; spread half over dough.

title: guava cheesecake delight
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat	into
a 9 1/2 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.	Cool.

title: sausage and stuffing appetizer
directions: Melt butter with water.
Stir in stuffing mix, egg and sausage. Mix with hand.
Shape into balls.
Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap meat mixture in bacon; fasten with a toothpick.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: pistachio ice cream
directions: Mix the cornstarch and sugar in a saucepan.
Stir in the milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Stir this mixture into the eggs, then return mixture to the saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture thickens (it must not be allowed to boil), then remove from heat and let cool.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients, except salsa; spread on tortillas.
Roll up and chill.
Cut tortillas in 3/4-inch slices and serve with salsa for dipping.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cowboy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: delicious pumpkin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs.
Add oil and pumpkin, beat until smooth.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Gradually beat into pumpkin mixture.
Pour batter into five greased 5 inch by 2 1/2 inch by 2 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325 degree oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks.

title: pineapple trifle
directions: In a saucepan off heat, combine milk and cornstarch until completely mixed. Add the sugar, egg whites and oil and cook over medium-low heat. Stir constantly with a wire whisk until thickened. Add extracts. Blend in and set aside to cool slightly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, vanilla, almond and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix real good.
Roll out on floured board and cut with cutters for whatever holiday.
Decorate with frosting and candies.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, baking soda and baking powder. Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Note that dough will be sticky.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes.
Taste like the biscuits at Red Lobster!

title: low calorie salad dressing or dip
directions: Mix.
Use as a salad dressing or dip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with cubed bread, then cover with chicken salad.
Put whole bread slices on top.
Mix half and half with eggs; pour over top.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, pour soup on top and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes, uncovered.
Put cheese on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken thighs until done.
Take chicken off the bone. Mix all the ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish.
Pour 1 can of mushroom soup over the top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: black forrest cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box, then add can of cherries.
Bake as directed.
When cake comes out of oven, spread fudge topping over cake.
Let cool, then top with ice cream, Cool Whip and cherries.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream jam and cream cheese together thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip; chill.
Thin with milk if dip becomes too thick.
Serve with chunks of fresh fruit such as strawberries, bananas, apples and pears.

title: brown gravy with no fat
directions: Bring water to a boil, add dry ingredients and simmer about 5 to 10 minutes for blending.

title: cloud cookies
directions: Beat egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating until peaks are stiff. Fold in the chocolate chips, then nuts.
Cover a baking sheet with white paper.
Drop cookie mixture on by the rounded teaspoon.

title: chocolate chip cherry drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, margarine, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: apple tarts
directions: Roll biscuits out thin.
Add 1 tablespoon of applesauce in middle of dough.
Fold dough over and crimp edges with a fork. Fry with butter in pan on top of stove.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant crosswise into 1/2 inch slices.
Combine mayonnaise, salt and onion.
Set aside.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Spread both sides of eggplant slices with mayonnaise mixture, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix water, salt, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring slowly to a boil.
When it begins to boil and thickens, add the second mixture of yolks, juice and rind.
Cook about 3 minutes longer.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Make meringue from the 2 egg whites.
Beat them until they hold a soft peak.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar, one at a time.
Spread on top of filling and bake about 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: gouflette(belgian cookies)
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, vanilla and melted butter. Add flour, cinnamon and soda.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waffle iron; bake until golden brown.

title: five layer taco dip
directions: Layer 1 is refried beans, taco seasoning mix and taco sauce. Mix well.
Layer 2 is chopped onion.
Layer 3 is sour cream, Miracle Whip, Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Mix well.
Layer 4 is cheddar cheese.
Layer 5 is lettuce and tomatoes.

title: sue's lasagne
directions: Brown beef in lightly salted skillet.
Mix the garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and sauce; add to meat.
Cover and cook on low for 15 minutes.
Slightly undercook the noodles.
Mix thinly sliced onions, cream cheese and sour cream.
Put 1/3 of the noodles (drained) in greased baking dish.
Spread with 1/3 of cheese mix and 1/3 of meat mix.
Repeat twice more.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Dust veal with flour.
Melt butter in pan.
Add onions and garlic and cook until yellow.
Add bouillon cubes and dissolve. Add mustard and paprika.
Stir and pour into a bowl.
Melt the other 4 tablespoons butter in frypan.
Fry meat on both sides. Pour onion mixture over it and cook 30 minutes over low heat. Stir in cream and bring to a boil.
Serve immediately over buttered parsley noodles.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine apples, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients, blending well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Batter will be very heavy.
Let age for 1 day before cutting.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each breast with bacon.
Cover bottom of flat greased baking dish with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken on chipped beef. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all.
Refrigerate all night. Next day, bake at 275° for 3 hours uncovered or until done.

title: sweet 'tater casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup margarine.
Beat until smooth.
Turn mixture into casserole dish.
In a bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and 1/3 cup margarine.
Crumble over potato mixture and sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon stickies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until well mixed (cream).
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating each 1 minute.
Add flour and milk alternately; beat well.
Add vanilla.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour 2 cups of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan; bake 15 minutes.

title: betty's chocolate chip delight
directions: Dip cookies in milk.
Put in casserole dish. Spoon Cool Whip over (may add nuts and cherries).
Layer cookies over Cool Whip. End with Cool Whip.
Crumble cookies on top.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: braised cheddar beef cubes
directions: Brown beef cubes that have been coated with flour, salt and pepper in Crisco in a large Dutch oven.
Add bouillon cubes, sauce, onion, celery seed and water to meat.
Cover; cook 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes.
Add brown sugar and cook 20 minutes more.
Add cheese and mushrooms and cook 10 minutes more.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: world war ii cake
directions: In a saucepan, mix brown sugar, 1 1/2 cups water, shortening, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Bring to a boil and continue boiling for 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Preheat oven to 325°.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread into buttered 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Col and ice with desired icing.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Save 2/3 cup each of chips and cheese.
Put in casserole; sprinkle with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, pumpkin and butter. Sift in all dry ingredients. Stir in nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chuck's spaghetti gravy
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet and set aside.
Chop celery; cut pepperoni into sections.
Add garlic and saute in bacon drippings until celery is soft.
Drain grease.
Empty 2 cans puree into large pot.
Use one can to measure water and add.
Add seasonings to taste.
(These may be added gradually as the gravy simmers.)
Crumble bacon and add.
Simmer minimum of 3 hours.
Add meatballs, sausage or chicken as desired.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Wash and core whole mushrooms; lay flat on baking pan. Sprinkle mushrooms with garlic.
Fill with Romano cheese.
Place a pat of real butter on each mushroom.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, sour cream and soda.
Beat very well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on a lightly greased or oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until they are light brown.
Makes 3 dozen cookies. These are soft and freeze well.

title: smith's beefeater spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach several times. Combine celery, onion, eggs and cheese. Mix with spinach. Mix well. Fold mayonnaise gently into vegetables. Garnish with grated egg. May serve with horseradish on the side.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Combine hamburger, onion, pepper and oil. Cook until tender. Add paste tomatoes and let simmer about 1 hour.
Cook noodles and drain.
Pour hamburger mix over noodles; stir.
Mix and serve hot.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Squeeze excess liquid from zucchini.
Mix all ingredients together.
Heat butter in pan.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of batter into pan; brown both sides.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into two balls.
If they seem too soft to hold their shape, add more grated Cheddar.
Roll in crushed pecans before serving.

title: banana punch
directions: Mash bananas with fork; sprinkle with lemon juice and set aside. Mix orange juice according to directions on can. In large bowl, combine sugar and orange juice with other liquids, except ginger ale. Add bananas and stir. Pour into 2 plastic gallon containers and place in freezer overnight. Let thaw 1 hour before serving. Cut through mixture to remove from container. Pour 1 container into punch bowl; stir until slushy and add 1 quart ginger ale just before serving. Repeat with second gallon.

title: peach crisp
directions: Slice peaches into well buttered dish.
Make crumbs of flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Crumble over fruit. Pour 1/4 pound melted butter over crumble mixture.
Bake at 350°, until peaches are tender and top is lightly browned, 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix raspberry and strawberry Kool-Aid with enough water to dissolve.
Add sugar, pineapple juice and frozen lemonade.
Pour into 1 gallon container.
Add water until container is 3/4 full. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind or mash all ingredients.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
While hot, place in jars and seal.

title: washington chowder
directions: Cook (fry) bacon or ham.
Add onions and saute until lightly browned.
Add potatoes, tomatoes, salt, pepper and water; simmer for 1 hour.
Add corn and cook 15 minutes.
Melt margarine; add flour and blend.
Add hot milk or nondairy creamer.
Stir until smooth.
Add margarine, flour and milk mixture to ingredients. Bring to scalding point, but do not boil.
Makes 10 servings.

title: velvet almond fudge cake
directions: Toast almonds about 5 minutes.
Spread 1/2 on bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Mix other ingredients.
Stir in chips and rest of almonds.
Bake at 350° for about 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain green beans, peas, corn and pimientos.
Add celery, green pepper and green onions.
Boil and cool sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add syrup and salt and beat well. Beat in eggs one at a time; add pecans. Stir in well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Place in 350° oven for 1 hour. Check by inserting a knife in center of pie. If clean, pie is done. Allow to cool well before serving.

title: sunday baked chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Coat chicken and place in a single layer in a baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and oil well. Pour in ungreased casserole dish. Mix brown sugar and cocoa and sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over all. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Stir cheese, then add first 4 ingredients.
Stir and add next 3 ingredients.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Thoroughly mix tomato juice and seasonings.
Chill before serving.

title: harris kahlua
directions: Add sugar, coffee and vanilla bean to 2 or 3 cups hot water. Shake well.
Let set until well dissolved, about 1 to 2 hours, then add vodka.
Can drink plain or fill glass with ice and add 1/3 full Kahlua and add milk to top of glass.

title: so easy so good coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and water all together and bake in four layer cake pans in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Mix together coconut and sour cream.
While cake is hot from the oven, prick each layer with a fork.
Pour and spread sour cream and coconut mixture over each layer, stacking layers as you go.

title: hamlin's white sauce
directions: Chop olives and onion in blender until fine.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Thin with buttermilk to a salad dressing or dip consistency.

title: easy vegetable cheese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash peppers and onions; remove pepper seeds.
Put through food chopper or grinder.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes.
Drain well and put in large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until onions are transparent, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: chili(for burgers)
directions: Simmer first 2 ingredients until hamburger is brown. Add other ingredients and simmer until thickened. If using more than 1 1/2 pounds of hamburger, add some chili powder.

title: lemon cool whip pie
directions: Blend lemonade and condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and lemon juice. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: broccoli topped potatoes
directions: Blend and heat oil, flour and pepper in saucepan until smooth. Stir in milk gradually.
Cook and stir on medium to medium-high heat until mixture comes to a boil and is slightly thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in vegetables.
(Reheat on low, if necessary.)
Cut open potatoes. Top with sauce.
Enough for 8 potatoes.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in parsley.
Refrigerate for up to 24 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Pour oil into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients in pan; stir with fork or spoon until well blended.
Scrape bottom and sides of pan and spread batter evenly.
One-half cup each of raisins and chopped nuts may be added.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Follow package directions for doneness.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Makes 16 or more servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: spinach beef biscuit bake
directions: Press and flatten biscuits onto the bottom and up the sides of a greased pan (11 x 7 x 2) and set aside.
In a skillet over medium heat, cook beef and onion.
Drain grease.
While the hamburger is cooking, you can thaw the spinach in the microwave and also prepare the rest of this recipe, just remember to watch your hamburger.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add spinach and mushrooms to the eggs and mix well.
Stir in the cheese, garlic powder, salt, pepper and beef mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon into biscuit crust.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.

title: dad's chicken breading
directions: Mix ingredients.
Coat chicken with breading.
Brown chicken. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or 20 minutes on High in microwave, covered.
