title: country macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in water until done (approximately 10 minutes). Drain and rinse in cold water.
Mix all ingredients and add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour into pie crusts. Chill in refrigerator until gels.
Makes 2 pies.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix dry yeast, 1 teaspoon molasses and 1 cup warm water.
Let rise.
Mix 2 cups boiling water, oatmeal, 1/2 cup molasses and egg.
Set aside to cool while top mixture is rising.
Mix the two together, then add 5 cups flour; let rise.
Use 1 cup flour to knead in the dough.
Make into rolls or loaves.
Let rise again until just over your pan.
Cook for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt the butter in a small pan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook and stir over low heat until sugar melts.
Add milk.
Cool.
Beat by hand, adding the confectioners sugar.
Beat until smooth and thick enough to spread.
Add vanilla.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs; add dry ingredients.
Add carrots and nuts; add vanilla and mix well with mixer.
Pour into greased funnel cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: brown sauce
directions: Heat butter in small, heavy skillet over low heat until browned. add onion and saute until light brown. Remove onion. Stir in flour until well blended. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until flour is a deep mahogany brown. Remove from heat, Gradually stir in stock. Bring to a boil stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute. Stir in seasonings. Makes 1 cup.

title: magic french fudge
directions: In top of double boiler; melt chocolate chips over hot water. Remove from heat; add sweetened condensed milk, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Stir until smooth.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Spread Doritos in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine soups, tomatoes, ground beef and mushrooms. Pour over Doritos.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cook in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: pink fruit freeze
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, ice cream and salad dressing. Mix until well blended. Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into 9-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Place in refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: two-bean chili
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, cook beef, green pepper, onion, chili powder and pepper until beef is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat. Add tomato juice, kidney beans and Great Northern beans.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce to low.
Cover; cook 20 minutes to blend flavors, stirring occasionally.
Top with sour cream.
Sprinkle with green onions and cheese.

title: dad's spareribs and juice
directions: Put ribs in a roasting pan and bake in a 275° oven for 2 hours.
Pour off fat.
Mix together all remaining ingredients and pour over the ribs.
Bake 1 hour more.
Serve in large bowl surrounded by the juice.

title: sour cream pie crust
directions: Combine sour cream, water, sugar and salt in a small bowl. Combine both flours in a large bowl. Cut in butter and shortening with fingers until coarse.
Add sour cream mixture and stir until dough forms.
Turn onto lightly floured work space. Divide in half.
Form each half into ball; flatten into disk.
Wrap each disk in plastic.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Can be frozen.

title: chili rico
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in large pan until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except pepper; boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in pepper; continue to simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes or until desired consistency.
Ladle into bowls and add additional picante sauce.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon sugar pretzels
directions: Place pretzels in a microwave bowl.
Mix oil, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and pour over pretzels.
Stir to coat.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, oats, onions, salt, pepper, tomato juice and egg thoroughly.
Pack into ungreased loaf pan.
Spread catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, then crushed potato chips on top. Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Cook Stove Top stuffing as directed.
Combine eggs, onion soup and mayonnaise.
Place layer of broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Add layer of cheese.
Pour small amount of sauce on top.
Repeat layers until all are used. Top with cooked stuffing mix.
Sprinkle butter or margarine on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: sausage hash brown bake
directions: In a large skillet, cook sausage over medium heat until no longer pink; drain on paper towel.
In a large bowl combine 1 3/4 cups cheese and the soup, sour cream, French onion dip, onion, green pepper, red pepper and pepper.
Fold into hash brown potatoes.
Spread half into a greased shallow 3 quart baking dish. Top with sausage and remaining potatoes mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Uncover, bake 10 minutes longer or until heated through.
Serves 10-12.

title: pineapple-lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: date nut balls
directions: In a skillet, melt margarine; then add sugar, egg and dates. Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil (10 to 12 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
With wet hands, roll a teaspoon of mixture into a ball. Roll in shredded coconut.

title: spinach soup
directions: Bring water to boil; add spinach.
Bring water back to boil. Remove from heat and ladle spinach from water; drain and press out moisture.
Chop finely.
Toss onion into flour.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion; cook until onion wilts (2 to 3 minutes). Slowly add stock and stir constantly.
Slowly add milk; cook until slightly thickened.
Add spinach; reheat.
Season with salt and a few grains of nutmeg.
Serve with Parmesan cheese over top.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer graham crackers.
Beat pudding with milk and cream cheese until stiff.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over crackers. Place another layer of crackers on top and add remaining pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of crackers. Drizzle or spoon frosting over top. Chill several hours.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix and keep in covered container.

title: polenta
directions: Place water, butter and garlic in large pot; reduce to a simmer.
Slowly add corn meal, whisking all the while.
Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring frequently, for 20 to 25 minutes. Add salt and pepper (to taste) and tomatoes; stir.
Remove from heat; pour into a large, buttered flat baking dish (or two 9-inch pie plates).
Garnish with nuts and parsley or basil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar. Add eggs and mix well. Add flour, salt, soda, sour cream, bananas and nuts. Mix well. Grease 2 small loaf pans. Pour in mixture. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Bananas can be frozen if not ready to bake yet.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Mix all
together
and put in large crock-pot.	Dot top with butter or
margarine.
Cover
and cook on low heat 6 to 8 hours. A very moist dressing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Break broccoli into flowerets and slice stems; place in baking dish.
Combine eggs, mayo, soup and 1/2 cup of the cheese and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheddar cheese over top.

title: southern pecans
directions: Combine sugars, syrup and milk.
Cook to soft-ball (234°). Cool 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat by hand about 2 minutes. Add pecans and beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Drop on foil or buttered wax paper.
Add teaspoon or so of hot water if necessary.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Cook fresh corn in 1 cup boiling salted water for 2 or 3 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Combine corn, evaporated milk, egg, onion, salt and pepper and 3/4 cup of cheese.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with oleo or butter and the remaining cheese, 1/4 cup.
Sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes. Garnish with green pepper rings.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: black walnut taffy
directions: Bring sugar, milk, Karo and paraffin to a boil in large kettle then add gelatin that has been soaked in the water.
Cook stirring constantly until it reaches 260° by candy thermometer.
Remove from fire and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased pans to cool.
Pull fast until light in color.
FUN for the "old-fashioned" taffy pull!

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Blanch cleaned and deseeded bell peppers.
Brown meat and drain well.
Add all ingredients except cheeses.
Cool.
Add cheese and stuff peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: scones
directions: Blend first four ingredients together.
Add raisins.
Blend in, then add milk.
Blend until a ball forms.
Place on floured board and knead for a few minutes.
Cut in half, make two circles. Flatten to about 2 inches thick.
Cut through each circle into eighths.
Place on greased sheet pan.
Separate wedges slightly. Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creamed peas
directions: Cook peas; drain.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil gently 2 minutes.
Add peas.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix all together and serve next day.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: blackberry sauce
directions: Combine berries, 1 cup water and sugar in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Combine 2 tablespoons water and cornstarch, mixing well; stir into blackberry mixture.
Cook 1 minute over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice; cool.
Chill.
Serve over angel food or sponge cake.

title: cornbread-sage dressing
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and soda; stirring lightly.
Add buttermilk and eggs, mixing well.
Stir in chopped celery and onion.
Heat bacon drippings in a 10-inch iron skillet until very hot.
Add 1 tablespoon drippings to batter, mixing well.
Pour batter into hot skillet and bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until bread is lightly browned.
Crumble into a large bowl, add stuffing mix and sage.
Set aside.

title: freezer dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze.
Let thaw for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in pot with oleo and olive oil. Brown meat also.
If using roast, stick garlic buds in it.
Cut fat off roast and wash off.
Add other ingredients and cook slowly for several hours until meat (if using roast) falls apart.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on bottom.
Add potatoes, carrots, bell pepper, celery, onions and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. To brown chicken, remove it carefully and place on top of vegetables and leave lid off.

title: crockpot roast beef or beef tips
directions: Place meat in crockpot.
Mix soups with 1 cup warm water, pour over meat.
Add more water to cover meat.
Turn crockpot on high, cook
8-10 hours.
The broth makes a rich gravy or you can use broth to cook noodles.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Blend in flour mixture.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick and cut out cookies.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet in hot oven at 400° until lightly brown, 5 to 7 minutes.
Cool before adding frosting.

title: chocolate chip cookie surprise
directions: Dip cookies in milk and layer in a 13 x 9-inch sheet pan.
Put a layer of Cool Whip on top of cookies.
Add another layer of the dipped cookies on top of Cool Whip.
Continue placing layers until pan is full.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve.

title: aunt fay's cherry cheesecake
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla. Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden.
Let cool.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Lightly brown pork (cut up) in oil.
Mix cornstarch and pineapple juice from can.
Put pork aside.
Put juice in skillet. Add brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and pineapple chunks.
Stir until thick (low heat).
Add pork, turn up heat and bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add tomato chunks last few minutes.

title: quick, easy & yummy dessert
directions: Whip the cream and add sugar and vanilla. Crush the graham crackers and fold into the cream. Use enough crackers to make the desired consistency. It is very rich, but so yummy!

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Wash potatoes.
Dry and cut in half crosswise.
Place in plastic bag, cut side down.
Leave end of bag open.
Cook on High for 10 minutes.
Remove skins and slice potatoes.
In 8-cup glass measuring cup or bowl, melt margarine on High for 40 seconds. Stir in flour, then milk, seasoned salt and pepper.
Cook on High for 3 1/2 minutes or until mixture thickens, stirring twice. Blend in Cheddar cheese.
Place cooked potatoes and onion in 7 1/2 x 12-inch glass dish; add sauce.
Stir and cover with waxed paper.
Cook on High for 6 minutes, exact cooking time depends upon thickness of sliced potatoes.
Top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Cook on High for 4 more minutes.
Serve.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: poor man's cheese torte
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Cool and don't let jell.
Beat cream cheese and sugar well.
Beat Carnation milk well.
Add cream cheese mixture and jello and beat at low speed on electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Chill until set.

title: apple grape drink
directions: Combine juice and lemonade, then chill. Stir in club soda and serve immediately. Makes 3-3/4 qts.

title: vietnamese cabbage salad
directions: Marinade:
Combine onions, vegetable oil, sugar, fish sauce, lemon juice and Vietnamese hot sauce.

title: sweet and sour doggies!
directions: Place all ingredients in large saucepan except for meat. Slice up hot dogs or kielbasa, then put in pot.
Can be put in a crock-pot or just cook on low heat for about 1 hour.
Great for kiddie parties!

title: orange smoothies
directions: Combine ice cream, milk and orange juice concentrate in food processor or blender; process until smooth. Pour mixture into glasses; garnish as desired.

title: squash delight
directions: Slice squash and boil until just tender.
Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and mix.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dilly beans
directions: Sterilize 4 pint jars.
Fill each with washed whole green beans.
In each jar, also add 1 clove garlic, 1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper and 1 head of dill.
On stove, bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over beans in jars.
Screw caps on.
Process for 10 minutes.

title: quick beef stew
directions: Trim fat from meat; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Combine meat and flour in a zip top plastic bag.
Close bag; shake.
Coat a 5 or 6-quart pressure cooker with cooking spray.
Add oil; place over high heat until hot.
Add meat; cook until browned, stirring often. Add carrots and the next 9 ingredients.
Close lid securely. According to manufacturer's directions, bring to high pressure over high heat (about 10 to 12 minutes).
Reduce to medium-low or level needed to maintain high pressure.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Run cold water over pressure cooker.
Reduce pressure instantly.
Remove lid so that steam escapes away from you.
Stir in peas and vinegar.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Combine sugar and cream cheese, beating until well blended. Beat in remaining ingredients.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Serve with purchased gingersnap cookies.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours until cake tests done.
Remove from oven and pour glaze over cake.
Let cake cool completely and remove from pan.

title: chicken in orange sauce
directions: In heavy skillet with lid brown meat in oil.
Remove chicken; add flour, cinnamon and cloves to drippings in pan and stir to a smooth paste.
Then add orange juice and Tabasco sauce.
Stir and cook until mixture thickens.
Add along with chicken, the almonds and raisins and simmer until tender (30 to 50 minutes).
Then add oranges and cook 5 minutes longer. Cook rice according to package. Serve chicken over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: gladys strange's um-um good potato salad
directions: Boil eggs and potatoes.
Put potatoes in refrigerator to chill completely.
Peel eggs and potatoes.
Dice eggs, potatoes and other ingredients; mix with jar of Miracle Whip in a very large mixing bowl.
Mix to desired consistency.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with chives.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until light brown and firm.
Turn oven off and leave sitting about 15 minutes longer.

title: velvety custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
At once, pour into unbaked pastry shell.
(To avoid spills, fill at oven.)
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake in very hot oven (475°) for 5 minutes; reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Serve cool or chill.

title: carlos' rice
directions: Saute onion, garlic, tomato and raisins to soften.
Add beer to rice so the level before cooking is about 1/2 inch above the rice.
Add all the rest of the ingredients; cook until all the beer is absorbed.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: my mama's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the corn.
Add corn and mix well.
Put in well-greased baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes in 400° oven.
Should be well browned on top.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice lemons as thin as paper, rind and all.
Combine with sugar; mix well.
Let stand 2 hours or preferably overnight, blending occasionally.
Add beaten eggs to lemon mixture; mix well. Turn into 9-inch pie shell, arranging lemon slices evenly.
Cover with top crust.
Cut several slits near center.

title: pasta with fresh tomatoes and herbs
directions: Fresh summer tomatoes and a variety of raw herbs make this fragrant dish tasty, beautifully presented, yet simple to prepare. The secret to this dish is absolutely fresh ingredients.
The tomatoes and herbs are never cooked, they are splashed with hot olive oil.
Any firm pasta may be used; we especially like large rigatoni (tubes), fusilli (bow tie) or spaghetti noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.
Excellent served as cold leftovers.

title: hamburger biscuits
directions: Brown the hamburger meat and onion.
Mix all together. Add pepper and salt.
Put in a baking dish.
Take a small can of biscuits.
Pull apart and put on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: day before casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in a large casserole dish and mix well. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil; sprinkle with paprika and brown top. Cooked chicken, turkey or tuna can be substituted for ham in this recipe.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, milk, corn syrup and butter in saucepan. Place over low heat and stir until mixture begins to boil.
Cook to soft stage (about 8 minutes).
Remove from heat and cool a few minutes without stirring.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until fudge loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered pan.
Slice when cool.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is very syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a roux with flour and shortening.
Add garlic and cook until golden brown.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery and cook until transparent.
Add shrimp and tomato sauce; simmer 10 minutes, stir in water and blend well.
Add all other ingredients except okra and oysters.
Cook 1 hour; add okra and cook 20 minutes.
Add oysters and cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve in a soup bowl over steamed rice.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream margarine with brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients and pecan meal.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased sheet, press flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: lipton california dip
directions: In a small bowl, blend the soup mix with the sour cream. Chill. Makes about 2 cups.

title: barbecue venison(for buns)
directions: Take a 6-quart pressure cooker, add 3 cups water to cooker. Salt meat a little; add venison.
Chop large onion over meat; add 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.
Put on lid and pressure for 45 minutes at 10 to 15 pounds pressure.
Take meat out of cooker.
Pull meat apart and chop well.
Place in baking dish; grate small onion very fine over meat.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and stir well until meat is covered.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve with buns.

title: oven spaghetti
directions: Cook 1 pound spaghetti and drain.
Pour sauce over spaghetti and stir well.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 325°.
Don't allow to bake dry.
Grate cheese over top.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple; bring to a boil.
Let cool until thick.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Add chopped pecans and mix well.
Let set until firm.

title: red and green cabbage salad
directions: Toss cabbages and onion together with any dressing.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time. Add sour cream after 2 cups flour. When all flour is blended, add vanilla (beat by hand) approximately 150 strokes.
Bake at 275° until done (when toothpick inserted comes out clean).

title: a #1 easy easy cream cheese frosting
directions: In bowl cream the butter and cream cheese together.
Add vanilla.
Add powdered sugar slowly while mixing until smooth. Let's frost.

title: wheat buns
directions: Place 1/2 cup butter and honey in a large bowl;
pour boiling water over both.
As mixture cools, dissolve yeast in warm water in a separate bowl.
When butter has melted and cooled, add egg, salt, and baking powder.
Stir in yeast.
Add flours alternately. Turn soft dough onto floured board;
knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl;
turn to grease top.
Cover with a damp towel and let rise until double in size, 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch dough down, turn onto floured board;
let rest 5 minutes.
Cut dough into 16 to 18 pieces; shape into rounds.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Flatten slightly. Brush tops with melted butter.
cover and let rise 30 minutes; until doubled in size.
Preheat oven to 400°F.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes until bun tops sound hollow when tapped.

title: smoked sausage and noodles
directions: In a large skillet, pour spaghetti sauce.
Add sausage cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Slice pepper and onion into rings and add to spaghetti sauce.
Let mixture simmer until onion and pepper are tender. Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and cream.
Add flour and eggs.
Alternate milk and flour.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 30 minutes; 325° for 15 minutes; 330° for 15 minutes.

title: curried rice
directions: Cook rice as directed on package (except decrease salt to 1/2 teaspoon) and stir in remaining ingredients with the water.
Cook until liquid is absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: banana nut bread(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mash bananas in medium bowl.
Sprinkle sweetener over bananas. Blend in eggs. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts, if used. Blend well, but do not overmix.
Pour into lightly greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 55 minutes. Remove from pan when cool.

title: italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in lemon juice, oil, salt and dressing.
Heat oven to 250°.
Crush crackers; roll chicken in crumbs.
Sprinkle water in the bottom of a shallow baking pan; add chicken.
Bake approximately 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and macaroni bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box; drain and set aside.
Saute ground beef, onions and green pepper until beef is browned; drain off fat.
Add tomato soup, cooked macaroni and peas to beef mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil the oleo, water and cocoa.
Mix flour, sugar and salt.
When first mixture boils, remove from heat and mix with dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Add eggs; beat well after each one. Add sour cream plus soda.
Pour into a well-greased 11 x 17 cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 19 to 22 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: diabetic cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into spring form pan. Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Melt together margarine and peanut butter.
Then add powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.
Form eggs with hands.
Set on foil or cookie sheet and chill for a couple of hours.
Melt chocolate and wax in a double boiler.
Roll eggs in chocolate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in mixer.
Add slowly the sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
In a large bowl, mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
Add flour mixture to the zucchini mixture and blend.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool.
Makes 3 small loaf pans or 2 large pans.

title: sweet 'n sour mini kabobs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On wooden toothpicks, alternately thread pineapple, chicken and green peppers.
Place kabobs in shallow baking pan and bake 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: mama harrison's fruit cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup pineapple in heavy pan and cook until thick.
Cool.
Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff. Beat yolks until frothy.
Sift together flour, nutmeg, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add cherries with juice, jelly, pineapple and egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in egg whites. Add raisins and nuts and stir well.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes, carrot, celery, onion, salt, pepper and milk in kettle with 1 1/2 cups of water.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Mash vegetables slightly into liquid.
Add milk and margarine and heat.
Add pepper and parsley.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: aunt frieda's cookies
directions: Add enough flour to be able to roll on floured sheet.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spread in bottom of oblong casserole dish.
Layer guacamole dip, sour cream, olives, tomatoes, onion and chilies.
Top with cheese.
Serve with white corn chips or your favorite nacho chips.

title: rich banana pudding
directions: Line bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch dish with vanilla wafers.
Cover wafers completely with sliced bananas.
Prepare pudding according to package.
Add milk.

title: spiced tea
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water, sugar, cinnamon and cloves; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; remove spices.
In a large bowl, pour mixture over the tea bags and let steep for 5 to 10 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Add juices.
Serve warm or cold.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: Combine milk, ground chuck, crumbs, onion, carrot, egg, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Shape into a 9-inch log on waxed paper.
Set aside.

title: purkey sloppy joe's
directions: Brown meat and sprinkle with onion flakes.
Add catsup, sugar, mustard, vinegar and stir well.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve on heated hamburger buns.

title: party potatoes
directions: Put in baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 cups boiling water.
Add sugar.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in 2 quarts warm water and combine.
Add one bottle lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Can be frozen until ready to use.
Add the ginger ale as it begins to thaw.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: fancy cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Form into a ball and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornstarch in a small saucepan; mix well.
Remove 1/4 cup of mixture.
Stir in the cornstarch and set aside.
Cook the juice mixture over medium heat until bubbly. Stir in the cornstarch mixture and continue cooking until smooth and thickened.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt over low heat in same pan the chips, butter and peanut butter.
Put Rice Chex in large bowl and pour chocolate mixture over it and stir to coat.
Add to powdered sugar in large brown grocery bag and shake gently.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: salmon pot pie
directions: Make white sauce by heating vegetable oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour, cooking for 1 or 2 minutes. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, and continue to cook until thick.
Add diced potatoes, salt, pepper and dill.
Remove from heat.
Add flaked salmon.
Mix well.
Line 8 x 14-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cans of the crescent rolls.
Pour the salmon filling into the dish.
Cover with the remaining crescent roll dough. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken liver saute
directions: Cut each chicken liver in half.
Put flour, salt, pepper, paprika and livers in a plastic bag and shake to coat.

title: betty's french salad dressing(in memory of betty schneider)
directions: Stir or blend in a blender.
Refrigerate.

title: cool dessert(mr. food)
directions: Add milk to pudding.
Mix all together.
Can add banana, peaches or strawberries. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Beat 1 egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough, 3 inches apart, onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for 2 minutes, then cool on rack.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions. Mix with above ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings at joint.
Put in large bowl with eggs, salt, pepper and cornstarch that has been combined.
After coating well, deep fry in oil until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Boil noodles; rinse and drain.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hungry-man casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In skillet, cook beef 3 minutes or until no longer pink. Remove to platter with slotted spoon.
Add onion to skillet.
Cook 3 minutes until softened.
Return meat to skillet. Stir in garlic, basil, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
In 2-quart baking dish, spread 1/3 meat mixture. Cover meat with 1/3 of the potato slices.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cheese, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper on potatoes.
Repeat for 2 remaining layers.
Pour broth over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour
until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Measure flour and run through sifter. Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Knead shortening with hands into mixture.
Pour in milk and knead until dough is soft and puffy. Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 10 biscuits.

title: skillet supper with italian sausage
directions: Quarter potatoes; put in 2-quart saucepan.
Add enough water to cover potatoes.
Add 1 teaspoon of salt.
Bring to boil over high heat, uncovered; reduce heat to medium and simmer until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain in colander.
In heavy skillet, heat oil.
Add potatoes; saute until browned, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Add onions, tomato, basil, oregano, thyme, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Saute until onions are limp, 3 to 5 minutes.
Put mixture in large casserole.
Brown the sausage and add to mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Broil 3 minutes until cheese melts.
Top with sour cream or yogurt if desired.

title: dilly green beans
directions: Cook beans and drain.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add broth, vinegar and dill.
Stir until bubbly, then stir in sour cream.
Add to beans and heat but do not boil.

title: porcupines(serves 6)
directions: Mix thoroughly meat, rice, milk, egg, onion, celery and seasonings.
Shape mixture into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls.
Place in one layer in casserole dish.
Mix together the tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce and pour over meat balls.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good served with vegetable lasagne or cheese lasagne, packaged or homemade.

title: spanish cabbage
directions: Pour oil over cabbage.
Stir until juice forms and cook until done.
Salt to taste.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine potato slices, sauce mix and amount of water and milk called for in potato mix package.
Add clam juice, onion and pepper.
Cover and cook 7 to 9 minutes, until boiling.
Stir and continue cooking 12 to 16 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring every 4 minutes.
Add clams, milk and butter.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until heated through. Enjoy!

title: cheese krispies(pennies from heaven)
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine until well blended. Add flour and salt. Fold in
Rice Krispies with hands and roll into small balls or flatten with thumb.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Should make about 250.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onions, salt and pepper.
Form into balls. Mix soup, water and Worcestershire sauce in Mirro pressure cooker.
Drop meat balls in pan and roll around in soup.
Cover. Set control and cook 8 minutes after control jiggles.
Cool pan normally for 5 minutes, then place under faucet until completely cooled.

title: congealed salad
directions: Chill half the mixture, then pour sour cream over the top and pour the other half on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Combine sugar and oil, then mix with dry ingredients.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: goulash casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown hamburger with onion and bell pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce after meat is browned.
Mix in soup.
Add salt and pepper for taste.
Pour meat and noodles in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Slice cheese on top and leave in oven until cheese melts.

title: tomato and rice soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Puree tomatoes in blender.
Add tomato puree, water, bouillon cubes, rice, thyme and pepper to onion mixture.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and cook 25 to 30 minutes, until rice is tender.
Yields approximately 7 cups.

title: fruit cocktail squares
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs and sugar at high speed until fluffy.
Add fruit cocktail, flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Spread into pan and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While hot, strizzle with glaze.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Combine yeast and warm water; set aside.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Add sugar, onion, margarine or butter, dill seed, salt, soda and egg.
When cool, add to yeast mixture, then add the flour.
Cover this soft dough and let rise in place for 1 hour. Stir down and turn into a well-greased 8-inch round casserole. Let rise in warm place for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Sprinkle with light salt. Makes 1 round loaf.

title: dilly toasted nuts
directions: In
a

microwave-safe casserole, combine butter or margarine, dill weed and celery salt.
Cook, uncovered, on 100%

to 40 seconds or until melted.
Stir in nuts.
Cook, uncovered, for 6 to 7 minutes or until
toasted, stirring every 2 minutes the first 4 minutes, then every 20 seconds.
Pour nuts onto a baking sheet;
spread out to cool. Makes 2 cups (8 servings).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, oatmeal, egg, onion, salt, pepper and tomato juice together.
Add desired amount of ketchup to mixture to get consistency you want, about 1 cup.
Place in baking dish.
Spread tomato sauce over the top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barb's cinnamon logs
directions: Mix
cream
cheese,
sugar
and egg.
Spread bread with mixture.
Roll
into a roll.
Using a pastry brush, coat rolls lightly with melted butter.
Dip rolls in a cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 20.

title: diabetic oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given; drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
If dough is chilled for an hour or so before baking, dough will be easier to handle.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Pack loosely in airtight container and keep in refrigerator.
To use take 1 cup mix and 1/3 cup milk or water.
Bake on cookie sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Bring water and sugars to a boil in a saucepan.
Add pecans. Boil to the soft ball stage (238° on candy thermometer).
Beat until creamy.
Drop in small mounds on a buttered platter.
For creamier candy, use milk instead of water.

title: fudge-fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Add dry cake mix and 1 1/3 cups hot water.
Stir with a fork until smooth.
Spread evenly in the pan.
Sprinkle dry frosting mix over all.
Gently pour 2 1/2 cups boiling water over frosting mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is shiny and cake starts to pull away from sides of the pan.
Serve warm, saucy side up, with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Beat well after adding one egg at a time.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° about 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly but well.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nuts; mix together well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into flowerets and dry in salad spinner.
Put raisins in water to cover; place in microwave.
Cook raisins on High for 1 minute.
When plumped, drain.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the broccoli, raisins and onion. Add small amount (half) of bacon.
Sprinkle rest of bacon on top.

title: fluffy cheesecake
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water for 1 cup.
Crush crackers.
Add melted oleo and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press one half into pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Cream cheese and add 1 cup sugar and pineapple and vanilla to jello.
Fold in whipped Pet milk.
Sprinkle with remainder of crumbs.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix together margarine, nuts, milk, sugar and coconut.
Get cold.
Make balls and let get cold.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips; blend together well.
Dip coconut balls into chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper until chocolate hardens.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add strawberries, then bananas.
Pour half in Pyrex dish and chill until firm.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together; spread over firm strawberry mixture.
Pour rest of Jell-O mixture over top and congeal.

title: rigatoni
directions: Cook rigatoni in salted boiling water.
Brown ground beef in large pan.
Add diced onions, pepperoni (slices cut in fourths), diced pepper, mushrooms and seasonings.
Stir until all is cooked. Add pizza and spaghetti sauces.
Grate cheese.
Drain rigatoni and add to mixture.
Place 1/2 of mixture into large casserole. Put 1/2 of cheese on it.
Put rest of mixture over this and finish with cheese.
Put in a 350° oven for 45 minutes with cover. Remove cover and brown cheese 15 to 20 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: cherry-coconut bars
directions: Mix butter, flour and sugar until smooth.
Spread thin with fingers in an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Stir rest of ingredients into eggs.
Spread over top of baked pastry.
Bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: banana chips
directions: Combine salt and sugar in a small bowl.
Peel and slice the bananas.
To each 3 cups sliced bananas, add 3 tablespoons of the sugar and salt mixture.
Mix well and fry in deep hot oil until golden brown.
Cool and separate sticking pieces.

title: texas matador
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Brown ground beef with salt, pepper and sugar in skillet.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and garlic and cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Add noodles, sour cream and cream cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: bob brevning's apple bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, apples and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 small ungreased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot with butter.

title: cheese ball
directions: Add cream cheese and dressing mix together and roll in bacon bits.
Serve with crackers.

title: old fashion creme pie
directions: Mix well.
In unbaked pie shell bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Time depends on oven.

title: old time syrup cake
directions: Pour sugar, oil and syrup in a bowl and mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Mix well.
Add soda to boiling water and pour into all ingredients and mix well. Pour cake into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a preheated oven.

title: comfort jeeplay's "meat on a stick"
directions: Place pureed jalapeno sauce in a large bowl.
Roll cooked meat and onion kabobs in this mixture (or brush sauce on with a pastry brush).
Enjoy plain or hot.

title: cauliflower bake
directions: Combine cauliflower, salt and water.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Cook about 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside. Combine butter, sugar, salt, pepper and cracker crumbs.
Stir in cauliflower, one cup of shredded cheese, onion, pepper and diced tomatoes and juice.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take out of oven and add remaining 1/2 cup shredded cheese and bake an additional 5 or 10 minutes. Delicious!

title: ice cream
directions: Whip the eggs.
Mix all other ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into freezer.

title: mexican cheese sticks
directions: Cut the block of cheese in half crosswise. Then cut each portion into 8
"sticks" (each measuring about 3 inches long, 1/2 inch wide and 1/2 inch thick). Combine flour, salt, and black pepper in a shallow dish.
In another dish, beat together the egg, milk, and Tabasco.
In the third dish, combine the bread crumbs and taco seasoning mix.
Coat each stick of cheese with flour, shaking off any excess.
Then place in egg and coat well. Carefully move the cheese stick from the egg and place in the seasoned crumbs, coating well.
Set aside until all cheese sticks are coated.
Place in freezer for about 30 minutes.
Heat oil to 375 degrees F.
Remove cheese sticks from freezer and dip into egg again and then give each another coating of crumbs.
Drop into hot oil and cook until delicately browned.
Remove from oil with a slotted spoon or use a fry basket for cooking them.
Drain well on absorbent paper.
Allow to cool slightly before serving.
Serve with salsa, if desired.
Makes 16 cheese sticks.

title: tomato pie
directions: Beat together mayonnaise, egg, egg yolks and spices.
Layer in pie crust in the following order:
both cheeses, chopped tomato, onion, mayonnaise mixture.
Dot top with butter.
Add Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sea legs casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; add pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
So easy!

title: heavenly sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, cottage cheese, sour cream, grated onion and salt.
Put
in
greased
casserole
and
add
melted butter and almonds.
Bake at
for
minutes.
Makes 6 servings. (This can be
prepared
a day ahead of serving-just be sure it gets hot after having been stored in refrigerator.)

title: cream cheese filled tortillas
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese, olives, chiles and onion.
Mix well.
Spread about 1/3 cup mixture to within 1/4-inch of the edge of each tortilla.
Roll tightly.
Chill until serving time, at least 2 hours.
Cut into sections and serve.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, cheese, garlic and parsley. Add bread crumbs (one cup, more or less) until the consistency of dough. Mix well. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Fry in olive oil.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Combine in electric blender and chop until completely mixed. Chill.
Serve over boiled shrimp on bed of crisp lettuce.

title: 4 layer chocolate dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: mrs. marple's b.b.q. ribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with Adolph's and refrigerate overnight.
Brown in skilled (don't need extra fat, ribs provide enough).

title: party pizza
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Chop cheese and heat on low until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put mixture on party rye bread and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: italian salad
directions: Toss all ingredients and allow to chill overnight.
Place in glass bowl and decorate with sliced salami and hard-boiled eggs.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add buttermilk, margarine and eggs. Beat at low speed with electric mixer until moistened. Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes. Spoon batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine remainder of brown sugar, pecans and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover next morning and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Serve warm.
Serves 12.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil, skin and chop chicken.
Combine ingredients, adding enough broth to blend well.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat red and green enchilada sauces in a medium pot.
Pour oil into a small skillet until it is about 1-inch deep.
Heat until a few drops of water splatter when added to oil.
Fry tortillas, one at a time, until softened, 3 to 5 seconds on each side.
Blot on paper towel; put into hot enchilada sauce for a few seconds. Fill each tortilla with cheese, about 1 tablespoon onions and 1 tablespoon chilies.
Secure with toothpicks.
Line up filled tortillas in a cake pan; cover enchiladas with remaining cheese, onions and chilies.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well and spoon into loaf pan.
Freeze overnight. Take from freezer at least 30 minutes before serving.
Slice into serving portions.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and beat.
Add butter and heat over low heat to melt.
Place peaches in pie crust.
Pour the filling over and bake at 325° for 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Make into 1-inch balls. Fry in skillet, using a small amount of oil.
Remove when done. Place balls in crock-pot or large pot on low heat.
Add barbecue sauce and preserves.
Let simmer for 2 hours, stirring occasionally, to keep from sticking.

title: california rangers
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugars, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, oats, coconut and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Form into small balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press lightly and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: throwed hot rolls
directions: Mix 1/2 cup warm water with yeast.
Mix eggs, salt, sugar and shortening with 2 cups warm water.
Add flour to mixture.
Let rise until it doubles in size in large bowl.
Work down.
Make into 3 balls the size of a jack or walnut.
Put into muffin pan and let rise.
Bake at 375° until brown.
To make sure it browns on both sides, use bottom rack.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash cooked sweet potatoes.
Add butter.
Stir until melted and blended.
Add pineapple, if used, or brown sugar and pecans. Place in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with marshmallows.
Bake at 375° until marshmallows melt and are lightly browned.
Serves 8.

title: wiener barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 1/2 hour.
Add wieners and heat thoroughly.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine 1 cup cornmeal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, bacon drippings and corn in a bowl. Set aside. Cook ground beef until lightly browned; drain well and set aside. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cornmeal in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle evenly with beef. Top with onion and cheese. Sprinkle peppers over top. Pour corn mixture over peppers. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Stir everything in together.
Knead for just a few minutes. Roll out or just drop by tablespoons onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400°
for 15 to 20 minutes.
You may mix dough and refrigerate for several days or freeze until time to bake!

title: apple yams
directions: Toss apples and nuts with combined brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate layers of apples and yams in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with oleo.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and broil until lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a baking dish. Bake 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: colored congeal salad
directions: Use a tube cake pan.
Congeal either flavor of Jell-O first with pears and cottage cheese.
Once jelled, pour in the other liquid Jell-O over the jelled Jell-O and refrigerate until jelled. Pour out for a ring figure or serve on lettuce.
Excellent when you want a pretty dessert.

title: mustard glaze for pork ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan except ribs.
If grilling ribs, rub them with rosemary and garlic, both sides.
Place on rack meaty side down.
Spread top with 1/3 glaze.
Cook until bottom side crisp, about 5 minutes.
Turn and spread top with 1/3 glaze, and cook until bottom is crisp.
Turn, top with remaining 1/3 and cook until top is glazed, about 1 minute.
Should be done by now.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, cottage cheese and taco mix. Spread onto a pizza pan.
Spread a thin layer of taco sauce over this.
Top in this order with shredded lettuce, diced tomato and shredded taco cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Mix all ingredients and spread in pan. Bake until golden brown (about 24 minutes). Cut into rectangular pieces, about 2 x 1-inch. Refrigerate any remaining pieces.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil, boil rapidly for 5 minutes, remove from heat and pour over popcorn, be sure your pan is big enough to stir well,
I use a large roaster, then bake in 250° oven 1 hour.
Make sure to stir every 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool well.
When done you can place in a container with a tight lid, it keeps well.

title: chinese egg flower soup
directions: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil in saucepan.
Add bouillon cubes; heat, stirring, until dissolved.
Mix 3 tablespoons of water, sugar, salt, pepper and cornstarch in small bowl.
Stir into boiling bouillon slowly; cook for 1 minute.
Reduce heat. Pour in beaten eggs, stirring until eggs cook into shreds.
Remove from heat.
Add green onions.
Serve at once.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° in well-greased and floured pan for 40 minutes.
Can be baked in Bundt cake pan.

title: honey float
directions: Dissolve honey in the milk. Add ice cream. Stir until part of the ice cream is dissolved in milk. Makes 1 serving.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, garlic and sugar. Marinate chicken wings overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish meat balls(svenska kottbullar)
directions: Saute onions in butter; soak the bread crumbs in the cream with the egg.
Combine spices, sugar, meat and onions and mix. Shape into small round balls and brown.
Keep warm.

title: creole and linguica rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and linguica with spices in saucepan.
Put aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan combine rice, margarine and water. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and cook 20 minutes.
Stir in onion, pepper and linguica with spices.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: delicious cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower head.
Place in 2-quart pot with 4 cups boiling water.
Add salt and vinegar.
Cook about 6 to 8 minutes until crispy done.
Drain cauliflower.
Rinse with cold water and drain well until free of water.
Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Cut off excess stems; place in large bowl.
Add olive slices and diced cheese.
Stir in salad dressing.
Add parsley flakes and nutmeg.
Mix well and keep in the refrigerator.
If you desire, you may use raw cauliflower instead of cooked.
You may also add more of the ingredients listed to your desire.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old country quiche
directions: Bake a single crust pie shell at 400° for 15 minutes. Melt butter and set aside. Fry bacon crisp.

title: 1-2-3 mexican casserole
directions: Empty cans of chili into slow cooker.
Unwrap tamales; remove paper wrappers and slice each into four pieces.
Add to chili; add on can of corn which has been drained.
Salt and pepper lightly. Do not stir, but distribute gently with a spatula.
Cook in slow cooker on high for 30 minutes to an hour, then turn to low setting; cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir again lightly.
Add cheese on top one hour before serving time.
Serve with corn chips.

title: saga's recipe
directions: Brown ribs in bacon fat on all sides.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 hours, covered, until tender. Thicken sauce with flour.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Combine raisins and crushed pineapple in a small bowl; refrigerate and let soak for several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Into a bowl, sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Cream shortening and butter or margarine in large bowl with an electric hand-held mixer.
Gradually beat in sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition; blend in jam.
Alternately add sifted dry ingredients and buttermilk to the creamed mixture, ending with dry ingredients.
Blend in pineapple, raisins and chopped pecans. Pour batter into prepared 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake jam cake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes until cake tests done.
Dust Kentucky Jam Cake with confectioners sugar and cut in squares.

title: no fat vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth and vegetables; cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yields 2 servings, 16 calories per servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and water.
Cook over moderate heat until clear.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Cool mixture.
Add strawberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until served.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass dish; put rice evenly in bottom.
Saute onions and celery in oleo until transparent.
Stir in soups, cheese and broccoli.
Mix well. Pour over rice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
A great pot luck dish.

title: our favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop spoonfuls onto cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: chef tell's bread pudding(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Pack about half the dry bread slices in bottom of buttered and sugared deep baking dish.
Add about half the apple slices. Sprinkle with raisins.
Add more bread slices, more apple slices and raisins.
Add custard mixture by pouring over the mixture (mix about 1 teaspoon cinnamon in custard mixture).
Bake in a 375° oven until slightly browned on top and custard is "set" (approximately 45 to 60 minutes).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind up cranberries.
Add sugar; mix and let set overnight.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in a baking pan.
Salt apples lightly, and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Dissolve sugar in the warm water, and pour over apples.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Layer asparagus in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle each layer with a few dry tarragon leaves, salt and pepper.
Add salad dressing and vinegar; marinate overnight at room temperature.
Drain and serve on lettuce leaves and top with mayonnaise flavored with a little of the marinade.

title: hobo bread
directions: Pour boiling water over butter (margarine), raisins and soda; let cool.
Put sugar in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salt; mix. Add cooled raisin mixture, then add flour; mix well.
Put into 3 (1 pound) well-greased coffee cans; fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with butter and honey, or cool.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: olde virginia wassail
directions: Combine and bring to simmer. Strain or use percolator or drip coffeemaker with spices in the basket.

title: peach yam bake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Cut in butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add nuts.
Arrange yams and peaches in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then sprinkle with marshmallows.
Brown lightly in oven.

title: ma-ma myrtie's chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa well.
Add milk to dry mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla and cook until thick.
When nearly done, add margarine and whip until margarine melts.
Pour in already baked pie shells or graham pie shells.
When cool, put Cool Whip on top and serve.
(If preferred, egg whites can be beaten for topping.)

title: oriental stir-fried vegetables
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli and cut in half.
Cut stalks into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add broccoli and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add salt, garlic and 1/2 cup of the chicken broth.
Cover and cook 3 minutes. Uncover and stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add sprouts, chestnuts, mushrooms and pea pods; stir-fry 2 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and eggs; set aside.
In another large bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda, ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix flour into creamed ingredients until dough is smooth.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Dip tops in sugar. Place 2 1/2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Put cabbage into previously boiled water for about 1/2 hour to soften and loosen leaves.
Cut thick center stem from each leaf.

title: butter sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo thoroughly with sugar and vanilla and lemon or almond flavoring.
Add flour and soda.
Put in rolls in fridge for 2 or 3 hours or overnight.
Slice and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Spoon int crust.
Add pie filling on top.
Cover with plastic from prepared crust package.
Chill.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup, paprika and pepper.
In a greased 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potato slices in overlapping rows.
Sprinkle with cheese; spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover with foil; bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight. Double for a party.

title: pecan pie ii
directions: Mix sugar with beaten eggs.
Add melted butter, Karo, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Melt butter and brown pepper, onion and celery.
Mix together tomato soup, paste, sauce and mushroom soup.
Heat ground beef in small amount of water and drain when cooked.
Add to sauce Worcestershire sauce and garlic; cook for 2 hours slowly.
Add salt and pepper, if desired.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle walnuts over cake mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve plain or with whipped topping.

title: frozen crunch torte
directions: Mix together rolled oats, brown sugar and melted oleo (or butter).
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Stir to separate mixture, making it crumbly.
Lightly stir rolled oats, crumble mixture, pineapple and coconut into Dream Whip.
Pack lightly in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares and freeze.
Another family favorite.

title: salsa verde dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Spoon salsa over bottom of dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with avocado, jalapeo and cilantro.
Serve with chips.

title: harvard beets
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Place on medium heat and add water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add margarine, salt and pepper. Blend in beets and heat through.
May add more sugar, if desired.

title: orange pineapple delight cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges and juice. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Pour 3/4 cup juice from crushed pineapple over cake while still warm. Mix pineapple with pudding powder and Cool Whip. Spread over cooled cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: carrot raisin mallow salad
directions: Mix together ingredients lightly; chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: icebox fruit cake 1
directions: Mix fruit and crackers until well coated.
Add water to marshmallows and make syrup (double boiler).
Add to fruit mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pack tightly in containers and cover.
Store in refrigerator.
If wine or sherry are used, add to melted marshmallows after removing from double boiler.
This mixture can be packed tightly in paper cups.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Mix together ingredients and drop with a tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.
You may double recipe if you like.

title: chicken salad
directions: Saute onions until transparent.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, flour, cheese, egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to mixture.
Fold in carefully with a large spoon. Bake in a glass baking dish (13 x 8 x 2-inch) at 375° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and reserve one third cup of this mixture for topping.
Press the remainder into pan with even thickness.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Dissolve pudding with 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix all ingredients in mixer.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: bacon and cheddar muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine Bisquick, milk, oil and egg. Mix well. Fold in cheese and bacon. Put in muffin pan. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in pineapple.
Cool.
Add buttermilk.
When partly set, add Cool Whip and nuts if desired.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough into 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Spread cream cheese over cooled cookie and add drained fruit.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: *Unpacked - loosely poured into measuring cup.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix until well blended.
Chill and use over any type cabbage slaw.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Cover and bake 6 hours at 300°.
Remove beef from pan.
Shred with 2 forks.
Return meat to sauce.
Makes about 20 sandwiches.
Serve on semi-hard rolls.

title: coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan.
Put frozen rolls in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pudding on top of rolls.
Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Drizzle over rolls.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cover with foil and let rise all night.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand in pan about 10 or 15 minutes.
Turn out on plate and serve warm.

title: justin roast
directions: With boning knife, cut into roast and use quarter garlic slivers to push into holes.
Cover roast with a sprinkle of cayenne pepper and salt.
Rub evenly over all of roast.
(Wash hands.) Lightly sprinkle with black pepper.
Place roast in a turkey-size baking bag and place in roasting pan.
Pour wine and sauce over roast inside bag.
Sprinkle chopped green onions over roast.
Place onion quarters, carrot pieces and potatoes over, around and beside roast.
Seal bag and with a large meat fork, poke 2 rows of holes into bag.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours, then check.
Should be very tender meat and potatoes.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Put in food processor or blender for 30 seconds. Let set overnight in refrigerator to let flavors blend. Dip your favorite fruits.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and bake for 20 minutes at 400° to 425°.
These can be frozen, then baked.

title: hamburger and kraut casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger with onion.
Add kraut.
Add cooked rice and tomato soup.
Dot with brown sugar and butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in a heavy pan.
Beat egg yolks; add milk, mixing well.
Stir milk mixture into dry ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool and then layer in dish with wafers and bananas.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, salt and fat until mixture is crumbly.
Add water and mix until pastry holds together.
Roll out dough to fit pan used.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Stir slowly into liquid. Cook; stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cherries to sauce.
Pour into baking pan.
Cover with pastry.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until pastry is brown.

title: sweet crisp green tomato pickles
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix lime and water and cover tomatoes.
Let stand 24 hours.
Rinse well and soak in cold water for 2 hours.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and food coloring. Drain tomatoes and add to sugar and vinegar.
Soak tomatoes in mixture overnight.
Bring to boil and boil for 40 minutes.
Pack in clean, hot jars and seal.
Makes 8 pints.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Combine cream cheese and hot mashed potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Toss shrimp in juice.
Mix dressing mix with cream cheese and sour cream.
Add shrimp.
Can be made using fat-free products. Best after sitting in refrigerator overnight.

title: mulled cider
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients except rum and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Remove spices and add rum just before serving, if desired.
Serve hot.
Garnish with additional cinnamon sticks if desired.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed.
Mix and chill overnight.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a 2 qt. pan, saute onions in butter until transparent. Add the 2 cans of beef broth soup and 1-3/4 cans of water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 c. Vermouth; stir well.
If you wish, water may be substituted for the Vermouth.
Heat through.
Put in bowls and top with croutons and a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a larger bowl blend sugar, oil, salt, potato starter, water and flour.
This makes a stiff batter.
Grease another bowl, add dough and turn it over so that it is greased on all sides.
Lightly cover with foil and let stand overnight.
(Do not refrigerate.)

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter in dish.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Pour flour mixture into dish and top with fruit.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 mins.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine all, except bacon and cheese, in blender.
Blend for 15 seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch square Pyrex.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: microwaved french onion soup
directions: Place onion and margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) 2 minutes; stir.
Cover and microwave until tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in broth, water and sauce. Cover tightly and microwave on High to boiling point, 8 to 10 minutes.
Divide 1/2 of soup among 4 bowls; add toast.
Pour remaining hot soup over toast; sprinkle with cheese.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: Place crushed cereal into shallow pan; set aside.
In a small bowl, beat egg.
Add milk, flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in batter and then coat each piece in the crumbs. Place in greased baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Do not cover or turn chicken while baking.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Top with a can of cherry pie filling.
Chill until served.

title: turkey chili macaroni
directions: Saute turkey, onions, pepper and celery until meat is no longer pink.
Drain, reserving juice.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery; drain.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour ingredients into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry pink divinity
directions: Bring water and corn syrup to boil.
Add sugar; cook until hard ball stage.
Wipe off crystals.
Beat egg whites with gelatin to peaks.
Pour syrup over this mixture.
Beat first with mixer, then spoon, until dull.
Add nuts. Drop on waxed paper.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat together the sugar and eggs.
Add milk and flour to cream of tartar and baking powder.
Add nutmeg and vanilla (don't make the dough too stiff).
Roll thin, cut and fry in hot grease.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in pan in the order listed.
Pour pie filling in pan.
Add pineapple on top of filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of pineapple.
Next add coconut and then nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot fudge chocolate cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in sheet cake pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo.
Mix sugar, cocoa and pecans.
Add cheese.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread in glass dish or pan.
Let cool and cut in squares.
This is good fudge.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix together.
Roll in wax paper.
Sprinkle with paprika. Chill.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Drain vegetables and water chestnuts good. Layer in casserole dish.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix
all dry ingredients with fingers until mixed well. Add 1 cup milk and mix to a paste.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add remaining milk.
Cook
in
top
of double boiler until mixture falls in globs
from
spoon.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Layer 1/2 of the ham, potatoes and onion in crock-pot. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Then put half of cheese over that. Repeat layers.
Spread undiluted soup evenly over top so air does not reach potatoes.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or on high 4 hours.

title: asparagus venetian
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In an 8-inch baking dish, arrange asparagus.
Drizzle with Lipton Onion Butter, then sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat pie
directions: Slowly brown onion, pepper, celery and meat in cooking fat, stirring constantly.
Add flour slowly, stirring constantly until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into shallow, well-oiled baking dish.
Cover with biscuits.
Bake in a hot 450° oven about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: alleene's raisin egg pie
directions: Pour hot water over raisins to fill cup; let set while you prepare the other ingredients.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together.
Beat egg yolks until lemony.
Add sugar mixture, then raisins, then vinegar.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Add to first mixture and fold in.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° to 325°; bake an additional 45 to 60 minutes in all or until custard is set.

title: sugar pie
directions: Warm milk; add in sugar and flour.
Put into pie shell and bake 1/2 hour.

title: 15-minute sundae pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir slightly softened ice cream until smooth.
Spoon the ice cream into pie crust and cover with plastic lid.
Place pie in freezer for several hours until hard.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz, broccoli and rice; stir.
Add mushroom soup and water; combine in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Very good!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Refrigerate several hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and season to taste with salt and pepper. Alternate layers of beef, onions and sliced potatoes in a casserole dish.
Pour mushroom soup, to which has been added 1/2 can of water, over the layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: vi's dump cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl sift the dry ingredients.
Make a well and drop in the eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and cooled margarine. Mix well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable oil. Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cream pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 egg until smooth.
When smooth, pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with nuts. In another bowl, beat 3 eggs, Karo, remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla and remaining 1/2 cup sugar. Pour over nuts.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: Blend the cooking oil, granulated sugar and brown sugar until mixed.
Add vanilla; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir together the flour, milk powder, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture until well blended.
By hand, stir in carrots and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a 10-inch tube pan or 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Invert on plate, sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add onion and seasonings.
Stir in (do not drain liquids) remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: glazed sesame chicken
directions: Brush chicken with corn oil on all sides.
Mix flavor enhancer and salt.
Sprinkle on all sides.
Place on rack in broiler pan on lowest rack in broiler.
Broil 20 minutes, basting with oil twice. Turn and broil about 20 minutes on second side.
Spread marmalade on chicken.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Broil about 5 minutes, watching carefully. Turn; spread with marmalade, sprinkle with sesame seed.
Broil about 5 minutes longer or until fork can be inserted with ease.
Serves 4.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Crush sandies and place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Slice bananas on top of sandies.
Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread cream cheese mixture over bananas.
Chill, then spread pie filling (mixed with lemon juice) on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Roll ground beef into balls.
Put in skillet and cover with water.
Cook until water cooks away.
Put meat balls in crock-pot. Drain pineapple and add pineapple to meat balls. Add barbecue sauce and simmer.

title: beef with tomatoes and peppers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with meat.
Marinate for 15 minutes.
Drain; reserve marinade.
Heat wok; add peanut oil. Sear meat quickly over high heat.
Remove meat.
Add oil if needed to stir-fry next 4 ingredients.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Add meat and marinate tomatoes and green onions.
Stir until heated through and slightly thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sift flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast to buttermilk.
Mix, roll and cut.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carl's two-egg cake
directions: Mix well. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: honeymooner's casseroles
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Press potatoes between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Grease 2 (8 ounce) casseroles.
Arrange potatoes evenly in bottom of each.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Add cheeses and ham.

title: baked lima beans
